126GCS_MAVLINK::GCS_MAVLINK(GCS_MAVLINK_Parameters &parameters,
127 AP_HAL::UARTDriver &uart)
128{
129 _port = &uart;
130
131 streamRates = parameters.streamRates;
132}
133
134bool GCS_MAVLINK::init(uint8_t instance)
135{
136 // get associated mavlink channel
137 chan = (mavlink_channel_t)(MAVLINK_COMM_0 + instance);
138 if (!valid_channel(chan)) {
139 return false;
140 }
141
142 // find instance of MAVLink protocol; the protocol_match method in
143 // AP_SerialManager means this will match MAVLink2 and MAVLinkHL,
144 // too:
145 uartstate = AP::serialmanager().find_protocol_instance(AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink, instance);
146 if (uartstate == nullptr) {
147 return false;
148 }
149
150 // and init the gcs instance
151
152 // whether this port is considered "private" is stored on the uart
153 // rather than in our own parameters:
154 if (uartstate->option_enabled(AP_HAL::UARTDriver::OPTION_MAVLINK_NO_FORWARD)) {
155 set_channel_private(chan);
156 }
157
158 /*
159 Now try to cope with SiK radios that may be stuck in bootloader
160 mode because CTS was held while powering on. This tells the
161 bootloader to wait for a firmware. It affects any SiK radio with
162 CTS connected that is externally powered. To cope we send 0x30
163 0x20 at 115200 on startup, which tells the bootloader to reset
164 and boot normally
165 */
166 _port->begin(115200);
167 AP_HAL::UARTDriver::flow_control old_flow_control = _port->get_flow_control();
168 _port->set_flow_control(AP_HAL::UARTDriver::FLOW_CONTROL_DISABLE);
169 for (uint8_t i=0; i<3; i++) {
170 hal.scheduler->delay(1);
171 _port->write(0x30);
172 _port->write(0x20);
173 }
174 // since tcdrain() and TCSADRAIN may not be implemented...
175 hal.scheduler->delay(1);
176
177 _port->set_flow_control(old_flow_control);
178
179 // now change back to desired baudrate
180 _port->begin(uartstate->baudrate());
181
182 mavlink_comm_port[chan] = _port;
183
184 const auto mavlink_protocol = uartstate->get_protocol();
185
186 if (mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink2 ||
187 mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLinkHL) {
188 // load signing key
189 load_signing_key();
190 } else {
191 // user has asked to only send MAVLink1
192 _channel_status.flags |= MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1;
193 }
194
195#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
196 if (mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLinkHL) {
197 is_high_latency_link = true;
198 }
199#endif
200 return true;
201}
202
203void GCS_MAVLINK::send_meminfo(void)
204{
205 unsigned __brkval = 0;
206 uint32_t memory = hal.util->available_memory();
207 mavlink_msg_meminfo_send(chan, __brkval, MIN(memory, 0xFFFFU), memory);
208}
209
210// report power supply status
211void GCS_MAVLINK::send_power_status(void)
212{
213 if (!gcs().vehicle_initialised()) {
214 // avoid unnecessary errors being reported to user
215 return;
216 }
217 mavlink_msg_power_status_send(chan,
218 hal.analogin->board_voltage() * 1000,
219 hal.analogin->servorail_voltage() * 1000,
220 hal.analogin->power_status_flags());
221}
222
223#if HAL_WITH_MCU_MONITORING
224// report MCU voltage/temperature status
225void GCS_MAVLINK::send_mcu_status(void)
226{
227 if (!gcs().vehicle_initialised()) {
228 // avoid unnecessary errors being reported to user
229 return;
230 }
231 mavlink_msg_mcu_status_send(chan,
232 0, // only one MCU
233 hal.analogin->mcu_temperature() * 100,
234 hal.analogin->mcu_voltage() * 1000,
235 hal.analogin->mcu_voltage_min() * 1000,
236 hal.analogin->mcu_voltage_max() * 1000);
237}
238#endif

240#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
241// returns the battery remaining percentage if valid, -1 otherwise
242int8_t GCS_MAVLINK::battery_remaining_pct(const uint8_t instance) const {
243 uint8_t percentage;
244 return AP::battery().capacity_remaining_pct(percentage, instance) ? MIN(percentage, INT8_MAX) : -1;
245}
246
247void GCS_MAVLINK::send_battery_status(const uint8_t instance) const
248{
249 // catch the battery backend not supporting the required number of cells
250 static_assert(sizeof(AP_BattMonitor::cells) >= (sizeof(uint16_t) * MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN),
251 "Not enough battery cells for the MAVLink message");
252
253 const AP_BattMonitor &battery = AP::battery();
254 float temp;
255 bool got_temperature = battery.get_temperature(temp, instance);
256
257 // prepare arrays of individual cell voltages
258 uint16_t cell_mvolts[MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN];
259 uint16_t cell_mvolts_ext[MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_EXT_LEN];
260 const uint16_t max_cell_mV = 0xFFFEU;
261 const uint16_t invalid_cell_mV = 0xFFFFU;
262
263 if (battery.has_cell_voltages(instance)) {
264 const AP_BattMonitor::cells& batt_cells = battery.get_cell_voltages(instance);
265 static_assert(sizeof(cell_mvolts) <= sizeof(batt_cells.cells), "cell array length not large enough");
266
267 // copy the first 10 cells
268 memcpy(cell_mvolts, batt_cells.cells, sizeof(cell_mvolts));
269 // 11 ... 14 use a second cell_volts_ext array
270 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_EXT_LEN; i++) {
271 if (MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN+i < uint8_t(ARRAY_SIZE(batt_cells.cells))) {
272 cell_mvolts_ext[i] = batt_cells.cells[MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN+i];
273 } else {
274 cell_mvolts_ext[i] = 0;
275 }
276 }
277 /*
278 now adjust voltages to cope with two things:
279 1) we may be reporting sag corrected voltage
280 2) the battery may have more cells than can be reported by the backend, so the actual voltage may be higher than the sum
281 */
282 const float voltage_mV = battery.gcs_voltage(instance) * 1e3f;
283 float voltage_mV_sum = 0;
284 uint8_t non_zero_cell_count = 0;
285 for (uint8_t i=0; i<MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN; i++) {
286 if (cell_mvolts[i] > 0 && cell_mvolts[i] != invalid_cell_mV) {
287 non_zero_cell_count++;
288 voltage_mV_sum += cell_mvolts[i];
289 }
290 }
291 for (uint8_t i=0; i<MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_EXT_LEN; i++) {
292 if (cell_mvolts_ext[i] > 0 && cell_mvolts_ext[i] != invalid_cell_mV) {
293 non_zero_cell_count++;
294 voltage_mV_sum += cell_mvolts_ext[i];
295 }
296 }
297 if (voltage_mV > voltage_mV_sum && non_zero_cell_count > 0) {
298 // distribute the extra voltage over the non-zero cells
299 uint32_t extra_mV = (voltage_mV - voltage_mV_sum) / non_zero_cell_count;
300 for (uint8_t i=0; i<MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN; i++) {
301 if (cell_mvolts[i] > 0 && cell_mvolts[i] != invalid_cell_mV) {
302 cell_mvolts[i] = MIN(cell_mvolts[i] + extra_mV, max_cell_mV);
303 }
304 }
305 for (uint8_t i=0; i<MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_EXT_LEN; i++) {
306 if (cell_mvolts_ext[i] > 0 && cell_mvolts_ext[i] != invalid_cell_mV) {
307 cell_mvolts_ext[i] = MIN(cell_mvolts_ext[i] + extra_mV, max_cell_mV);
308 }
309 }
310 }
311 } else {
312 // for battery monitors that cannot provide voltages for individual cells the battery's total voltage is put into the first cell
313 // if the total voltage cannot fit into a single field, the remainder into subsequent fields.
314 // the GCS can then recover the pack voltage by summing all non ignored cell values an we can report a pack up to 655.34 V
315 float voltage_mV = battery.gcs_voltage(instance) * 1e3f;
316 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_LEN; i++) {
317 if (voltage_mV < 0.001f) {
318 // too small to send to the GCS, set it to the no cell value
319 cell_mvolts[i] = UINT16_MAX;
320 } else {
321 cell_mvolts[i] = MIN(voltage_mV, max_cell_mV); // Can't send more then UINT16_MAX - 1 in a cell
322 voltage_mV -= max_cell_mV;
323 }
324 }
325 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < MAVLINK_MSG_BATTERY_STATUS_FIELD_VOLTAGES_EXT_LEN; i++) {
326 cell_mvolts_ext[i] = 0;
327 }
328 }
329
330 float current, consumed_mah, consumed_wh;
331 const int8_t percentage = battery_remaining_pct(instance);
332
333 if (battery.current_amps(current, instance)) {
334 current = constrain_float(current * 100,-INT16_MAX,INT16_MAX);
335 } else {
336 current = -1;
337 }
338 if (!battery.consumed_mah(consumed_mah, instance)) {
339 consumed_mah = -1;
340 }
341 if (battery.consumed_wh(consumed_wh, instance)) {
342 consumed_wh *= 36;
343 } else {
344 consumed_wh = -1;
345 }
346 uint32_t time_remaining;
347 if (!battery.time_remaining(time_remaining, instance)) {
348 time_remaining = 0;
349 }
350
351 mavlink_msg_battery_status_send(chan,
352 instance, // id
353 MAV_BATTERY_FUNCTION_UNKNOWN, // function
354 MAV_BATTERY_TYPE_UNKNOWN, // type
355 got_temperature ? ((int16_t) (temp * 100)) : INT16_MAX, // temperature. INT16_MAX if unknown
356 cell_mvolts, // cell voltages
357 current, // current in centiampere
358 consumed_mah, // total consumed current in milliampere.hour
359 consumed_wh, // consumed energy in hJ (hecto-Joules)
360 constrain_int16(percentage, -1, 100),
361 time_remaining, // time remaining, seconds
362 battery.get_mavlink_charge_state(instance), // battery charge state
363 cell_mvolts_ext, // Cell 11..14 voltages
364 0, // battery mode
365 battery.get_mavlink_fault_bitmask(instance)); // fault_bitmask
366}
367
368// returns true if all battery instances were reported
369bool GCS_MAVLINK::send_battery_status()
370{
371 const AP_BattMonitor &battery = AP::battery();
372
373 for(uint8_t i = 0; i < AP_BATT_MONITOR_MAX_INSTANCES; i++) {
374 const uint8_t battery_id = (last_battery_status_idx + 1) % AP_BATT_MONITOR_MAX_INSTANCES;
375 if (battery.get_type(battery_id) != AP_BattMonitor::Type::NONE) {
376 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(BATTERY_STATUS);
377 send_battery_status(battery_id);
378 last_battery_status_idx = battery_id;
379 return true;
380 } else {
381 last_battery_status_idx = battery_id;
382 }
383 }
384 return true;
385}
386#endif // AP_BATTERY_ENABLED

388#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
389void GCS_MAVLINK::send_distance_sensor(const AP_RangeFinder_Backend *sensor, const uint8_t instance) const
390{
391 if (!sensor->has_data()) {
392 return;
393 }
394
395 int8_t quality_pct = sensor->signal_quality_pct();
396 // ardupilot defines this field as -1 is unknown, 0 is poor, 100 is excellent
397 // mavlink defines this field as 0 is unknown, 1 is invalid, 100 is perfect
398 uint8_t quality;
399 if (quality_pct == RangeFinder::SIGNAL_QUALITY_UNKNOWN) {
400 quality = 0;
401 } else if (quality_pct > 1 && quality_pct <= RangeFinder::SIGNAL_QUALITY_MAX) {
402 quality = quality_pct;
403 } else {
404 quality = 1;
405 }
406
407 mavlink_msg_distance_sensor_send(
408 chan,
409 AP_HAL::millis(), // time since system boot TODO: take time of measurement
410 sensor->min_distance_cm(), // minimum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
411 sensor->max_distance_cm(), // maximum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
412 sensor->distance_cm(), // current distance reading
413 sensor->get_mav_distance_sensor_type(), // type from MAV_DISTANCE_SENSOR enum
414 instance, // onboard ID of the sensor == instance
415 sensor->orientation(), // direction the sensor faces from MAV_SENSOR_ORIENTATION enum
416 0, // Measurement covariance in centimeters, 0 for unknown / invalid readings
417 0, // horizontal FOV
418 0, // vertical FOV
419 (const float *)nullptr, // quaternion of sensor orientation for MAV_SENSOR_ROTATION_CUSTOM
420 quality); // Signal quality of the sensor. 0 = unknown/unset signal quality, 1 = invalid signal, 100 = perfect signal.
421}
422#endif // AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
423
424// send any and all distance_sensor messages. This starts by sending
425// any distance sensors not used by a Proximity sensor, then sends the
426// proximity sensor ones.
427void GCS_MAVLINK::send_distance_sensor()
428{
429#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
430 RangeFinder *rangefinder = RangeFinder::get_singleton();
431 if (rangefinder == nullptr) {
432 return;
433 }
434
435 // if we have a proximity backend that utilizes rangefinders cull
436 // sending them here, and allow the later proximity code to manage
437 // them
438 bool filter_possible_proximity_sensors = false;
439
440#if HAL_PROXIMITY_ENABLED
441 AP_Proximity *proximity = AP_Proximity::get_singleton();
442 if (proximity != nullptr) {
443 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < proximity->num_sensors(); i++) {
444#if AP_PROXIMITY_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
445 if (proximity->get_type(i) == AP_Proximity::Type::RangeFinder) {
446 filter_possible_proximity_sensors = true;
447 }
448#endif
449 }
450 }
451#endif
452
453 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < RANGEFINDER_MAX_INSTANCES; i++) {
454 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, DISTANCE_SENSOR)) {
455 return;
456 }
457 AP_RangeFinder_Backend *sensor = rangefinder->get_backend(i);
458 if (sensor == nullptr) {
459 continue;
460 }
461 enum Rotation orient = sensor->orientation();
462 if (!filter_possible_proximity_sensors ||
463 (orient > ROTATION_YAW_315 && orient != ROTATION_PITCH_90)) {
464 send_distance_sensor(sensor, i);
465 }
466 }
467#endif // AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
468
469#if HAL_PROXIMITY_ENABLED
470 send_proximity();
471#endif
472}
473
474#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
475void GCS_MAVLINK::send_rangefinder() const
476{
477 RangeFinder *rangefinder = RangeFinder::get_singleton();
478 if (rangefinder == nullptr) {
479 return;
480 }
481 AP_RangeFinder_Backend *s = rangefinder->find_instance(ROTATION_PITCH_270);
482 if (s == nullptr) {
483 return;
484 }
485 mavlink_msg_rangefinder_send(
486 chan,
487 s->distance(),
488 s->voltage_mv() * 0.001f);
489}
490#endif
491
492#if HAL_PROXIMITY_ENABLED
493void GCS_MAVLINK::send_proximity()
494{
495 AP_Proximity *proximity = AP_Proximity::get_singleton();
496 if (proximity == nullptr) {
497 return; // this is wrong, but pretend we sent data and don't requeue
498 }
499
500 // get min/max distances
501 const uint16_t dist_min = (uint16_t)(proximity->distance_min() * 100.0f); // minimum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
502 const uint16_t dist_max = (uint16_t)(proximity->distance_max() * 100.0f); // maximum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
503
504 // send horizontal distances
505 if (proximity->get_status() == AP_Proximity::Status::Good) {
506 Proximity_Distance_Array dist_array;
507 if (proximity->get_horizontal_distances(dist_array)) {
508 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < PROXIMITY_MAX_DIRECTION; i++) {
509 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, DISTANCE_SENSOR)) {
510 return;
511 }
512 if (dist_array.valid(i)) {
513 proximity_ever_valid_bitmask |= (1U << i);
514 } else if (!(proximity_ever_valid_bitmask & (1U << i))) {
515 // we've never sent this distance out, so we don't
516 // need to send an invalid one.
517 continue;
518 }
519 mavlink_msg_distance_sensor_send(
520 chan,
521 AP_HAL::millis(), // time since system boot
522 dist_min, // minimum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
523 dist_max, // maximum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
524 (uint16_t)(dist_array.distance[i] * 100.0f), // current distance reading
525 MAV_DISTANCE_SENSOR_LASER, // type from MAV_DISTANCE_SENSOR enum
526 PROXIMITY_SENSOR_ID_START + i, // onboard ID of the sensor
527 dist_array.orientation[i], // direction the sensor faces from MAV_SENSOR_ORIENTATION enum
528 0, // Measurement covariance in centimeters, 0 for unknown / invalid readings
529 0, 0, nullptr, 0);
530 }
531 }
532 }
533
534 // send upward distance
535 float dist_up;
536 if (proximity->get_upward_distance(dist_up)) {
537 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, DISTANCE_SENSOR)) {
538 return;
539 }
540 mavlink_msg_distance_sensor_send(
541 chan,
542 AP_HAL::millis(), // time since system boot
543 dist_min, // minimum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
544 dist_max, // maximum distance the sensor can measure in centimeters
545 (uint16_t)(dist_up * 100.0f), // current distance reading
546 MAV_DISTANCE_SENSOR_LASER, // type from MAV_DISTANCE_SENSOR enum
547 PROXIMITY_SENSOR_ID_START + PROXIMITY_MAX_DIRECTION + 1, // onboard ID of the sensor
548 MAV_SENSOR_ROTATION_PITCH_90, // direction upwards
549 0, // Measurement covariance in centimeters, 0 for unknown / invalid readings
550 0, 0, nullptr, 0);
551 }
552}
553#endif // HAL_PROXIMITY_ENABLED
554
555// report AHRS2 state
556void GCS_MAVLINK::send_ahrs2()
557{
558#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
559 const AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
560 Vector3f euler;
561 Location loc {};
562 // we want one or both of these, use | to avoid short-circuiting:
563 if (uint8_t(ahrs.get_secondary_attitude(euler)) |
564 uint8_t(ahrs.get_secondary_position(loc))) {
565 mavlink_msg_ahrs2_send(chan,
566 euler.x,
567 euler.y,
568 euler.z,
569 loc.alt*1.0e-2f,
570 loc.lat,
571 loc.lng);
572 }
573#endif
574}
575
576MissionItemProtocol *GCS::get_prot_for_mission_type(const MAV_MISSION_TYPE mission_type) const
577{
578 if (mission_type >= ARRAY_SIZE(missionitemprotocols)) {
579 return nullptr;
580 }
581 return missionitemprotocols[mission_type];
582}

584// handle a request for the number of items we have stored for a mission type:
585void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_request_list(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
586{
587 // decode
588 mavlink_mission_request_list_t packet;
589 mavlink_msg_mission_request_list_decode(&msg, &packet);
590
591 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type((MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type);
592 if (prot == nullptr) {
593 mavlink_msg_mission_ack_send(chan,
594 msg.sysid,
595 msg.compid,
596 MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED,
597 packet.mission_type);
598 return;
599 }
600
601 prot->handle_mission_request_list(*this, packet, msg);
602}
603
604/*
605 handle a MISSION_REQUEST mavlink packet
606 */
607void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_request_int(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
608{
609 // decode
610 mavlink_mission_request_int_t packet;
611 mavlink_msg_mission_request_int_decode(&msg, &packet);
612
613 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type((MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type);
614 if (prot == nullptr) {
615 return;
616 }
617 prot->handle_mission_request_int(*this, packet, msg);
618}

620#if AP_MAVLINK_MSG_MISSION_REQUEST_ENABLED
621void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_request(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
622{
623 // decode
624 mavlink_mission_request_t packet;
625 mavlink_msg_mission_request_decode(&msg, &packet);
626
627 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type((MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type);
628 if (prot == nullptr) {
629 return;
630 }
631 prot->handle_mission_request(*this, packet, msg);

634
635// returns a MISSION_STATE numeration value best describing out
636// current mission state.
637MISSION_STATE GCS_MAVLINK::mission_state(const AP_Mission &mission) const
638{
639 if (mission.num_commands() < 2) { // 1 means just home is present
640 return MISSION_STATE_NO_MISSION;
641 }
642 switch (mission.state()) {
643 case AP_Mission::mission_state::MISSION_STOPPED:
644 return MISSION_STATE_NOT_STARTED;
645 case AP_Mission::mission_state::MISSION_RUNNING:
646 return MISSION_STATE_ACTIVE;
647 case AP_Mission::mission_state::MISSION_COMPLETE:
648 return MISSION_STATE_COMPLETE;
649 }
650
651 // compiler ensures we can't get here as no default case in above enumeration
652
653 return MISSION_STATE_UNKNOWN;
654}
655
656void GCS_MAVLINK::send_mission_current(const class AP_Mission &mission, uint16_t seq)
657{
658 auto num_commands = mission.num_commands();
659 if (num_commands > 0) {
660 // exclude home location from the count; see message definition.
661 num_commands -= 1;
662 }
663
664#if AP_VEHICLE_ENABLED
665 const uint8_t mission_mode = AP::vehicle()->current_mode_requires_mission() ? 1 : 0;
666#else
667 const uint8_t mission_mode = 0;
668#endif
669
670 mavlink_msg_mission_current_send(
671 chan,
672 seq,
673 num_commands, // total
674 mission_state(mission), // mission_state
675 mission_mode); // mission_mode
676}
677
678#if AP_MAVLINK_MISSION_SET_CURRENT_ENABLED
679/*
680 handle a MISSION_SET_CURRENT mavlink packet
681
682 Note that there exists a relatively new mavlink DO command,
683 MAV_CMD_DO_SET_MISSION_CURRENT which provides an acknowledgement
684 that the command has been received, rather than the GCS having to
685 rely on getting back an identical sequence number as some currently
686 do.
687 */
688void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_set_current(AP_Mission &mission, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
689{
690 // send_received_message_deprecation_warning("MISSION_SET_CURRENT");
691
692 // decode
693 mavlink_mission_set_current_t packet;
694 mavlink_msg_mission_set_current_decode(&msg, &packet);
695
696 // set current command
697 if (mission.set_current_cmd(packet.seq)) {
698 // because MISSION_SET_CURRENT is a message not a command,
699 // there is not ACK associated with us successfully changing
700 // our waypoint. Some GCSs use the fact we return exactly the
701 // same mission sequence number in this packet as an ACK - so
702 // if they send a MISSION_SET_CURRENT with seq number of 4
703 // then they expect to receive a MISSION_CURRENT message with
704 // exactly that sequence number in it, even if ArduPilot never
705 // actually holds that as a sequence number (e.g. packet.seq==0).
706 if (HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, MISSION_CURRENT)) {
707 send_mission_current(mission, packet.seq);
708 } else {
709 // schedule it for later:
710 send_message(MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT);
711 }
712 }
713}
714#endif // AP_MAVLINK_MISSION_SET_CURRENT_ENABLED
715
716/*
717 handle a MISSION_COUNT mavlink packet
718 */
719void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_count(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
720{
721 // decode
722 mavlink_mission_count_t packet;
723 mavlink_msg_mission_count_decode(&msg, &packet);
724
725 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type((MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type);
726 if (prot == nullptr) {
727 mavlink_msg_mission_ack_send(chan,
728 msg.sysid,
729 msg.compid,
730 MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED,
731 packet.mission_type);
732 return;
733 }
734
735 prot->handle_mission_count(*this, packet, msg);
736}
737
738/*
739 handle a MISSION_CLEAR_ALL mavlink packet
740 */
741void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_clear_all(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
742{
743 // decode
744 mavlink_mission_clear_all_t packet;
745 mavlink_msg_mission_clear_all_decode(&msg, &packet);
746
747 const MAV_MISSION_TYPE mission_type = (MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type;
748 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type(mission_type);
749 if (prot == nullptr) {
750 send_mission_ack(msg, mission_type, MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED);
751 return;
752 }
753
754 prot->handle_mission_clear_all(*this, msg);
755}
756
757bool GCS_MAVLINK::requesting_mission_items() const
758{
759 for (const auto *prot : gcs().missionitemprotocols) {
760 if (prot && prot->receiving && prot->active_link_is(this)) {
761 return true;
762 }
763 }
764 return false;
765}
766
767void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_write_partial_list(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
768{
769 // decode
770 mavlink_mission_write_partial_list_t packet;
771 mavlink_msg_mission_write_partial_list_decode(&msg, &packet);
772
773 MissionItemProtocol *use_prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type((MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type);
774 if (use_prot == nullptr) {
775 send_mission_ack(msg, (MAV_MISSION_TYPE)packet.mission_type, MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED);
776 return;
777 }
778 use_prot->handle_mission_write_partial_list(*this, msg, packet);
779}

810void GCS_MAVLINK::send_text(MAV_SEVERITY severity, const char *fmt, ...) const
811{
812 va_list arg_list;
813 va_start(arg_list, fmt);
814 gcs().send_textv(severity, fmt, arg_list, (1<<chan));
815 va_end(arg_list);
816}
817
818float GCS_MAVLINK::telemetry_radio_rssi()
819{
820 if (AP_HAL::millis() - last_radio_status.received_ms > 5000) {
821 // telemetry radio has disappeared?!
822 return 0;
823 }
824 if (last_radio_status.rssi == 255) {
825 // see RADIO_STATUS packet definition
826 return 0;
827 }
828 return last_radio_status.rssi/254.0f;
829}
830
831void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_radio_status(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
832{
833 mavlink_radio_t packet;
834 mavlink_msg_radio_decode(&msg, &packet);
835
836 const uint32_t now = AP_HAL::millis();
837
838 last_radio_status.received_ms = now;
839 last_radio_status.rssi = packet.rssi;
840
841 // record if the GCS has been receiving radio messages from
842 // the aircraft
843 if (packet.remrssi != 0) {
844 last_radio_status.remrssi_ms = now;
845 }
846
847 last_txbuf = packet.txbuf;
848
849 // use the state of the transmit buffer in the radio to
850 // control the stream rate, giving us adaptive software
851 // flow control
852 if (packet.txbuf < 20 && stream_slowdown_ms < 2000) {
853 // we are very low on space - slow down a lot
854 stream_slowdown_ms += 60;
855 } else if (packet.txbuf < 50 && stream_slowdown_ms < 2000) {
856 // we are a bit low on space, slow down slightly
857 stream_slowdown_ms += 20;
858 } else if (packet.txbuf > 95 && stream_slowdown_ms > 200) {
859 // the buffer has plenty of space, speed up a lot
860 stream_slowdown_ms -= 40;
861 } else if (packet.txbuf > 90 && stream_slowdown_ms != 0) {
862 // the buffer has enough space, speed up a bit
863 if (stream_slowdown_ms > 20) {
864 stream_slowdown_ms -= 20;
865 } else {
866 stream_slowdown_ms = 0;
867 }
868 }
869
870#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
871 if (stream_slowdown_ms > max_slowdown_ms) {
872 max_slowdown_ms = stream_slowdown_ms;
873 }
874#endif
875
876#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
877 //log rssi, noise, etc if logging Performance monitoring data
878 if (AP::logger().should_log(log_radio_bit())) {
879 AP::logger().Write_Radio(packet);
880 }
881#endif
882}
883
884void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_mission_item(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
885{
886 mavlink_mission_item_int_t mission_item_int;
887 bool send_mission_item_warning = false;
888 if (msg.msgid == MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_ITEM) {
889 mavlink_mission_item_t mission_item;
890 mavlink_msg_mission_item_decode(&msg, &mission_item);
891#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
892 MAV_MISSION_RESULT ret = AP_Mission::convert_MISSION_ITEM_to_MISSION_ITEM_INT(mission_item, mission_item_int);
893 if (ret != MAV_MISSION_ACCEPTED) {
894 const MAV_MISSION_TYPE type = (MAV_MISSION_TYPE)mission_item_int.mission_type;
895 send_mission_ack(msg, type, ret);
896 return;
897 }
898#else
899 // No mission library, so we can't convert from MISSION_ITEM
900 // to MISSION_ITEM_INT. Since we shouldn't be receiving fence
901 // or rally items via MISSION_ITEM, we don't need to work hard
902 // here, just fail:
903 const MAV_MISSION_TYPE type = (MAV_MISSION_TYPE)mission_item.mission_type;
904 send_mission_ack(msg, type, MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED);
905 return;
906#endif
907 send_mission_item_warning = true;
908 } else {
909 mavlink_msg_mission_item_int_decode(&msg, &mission_item_int);
910 }
911 const MAV_MISSION_TYPE type = (MAV_MISSION_TYPE)mission_item_int.mission_type;
912
913#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
914 const uint8_t current = mission_item_int.current;
915
916 if (type == MAV_MISSION_TYPE_MISSION && (current == 2 || current == 3)) {
917 struct AP_Mission::Mission_Command cmd = {};
918 MAV_MISSION_RESULT result = AP_Mission::mavlink_int_to_mission_cmd(mission_item_int, cmd);
919 if (result != MAV_MISSION_ACCEPTED) {
920 //decode failed
921 send_mission_ack(msg, MAV_MISSION_TYPE_MISSION, result);
922 return;
923 }
924 // guided or change-alt
925 if (current == 2) {
926 // current = 2 is a flag to tell us this is a "guided mode"
927 // waypoint and not for the mission
928 result = (handle_guided_request(cmd) ? MAV_MISSION_ACCEPTED
929 : MAV_MISSION_ERROR) ;
930 } else if (current == 3) {
931 //current = 3 is a flag to tell us this is a alt change only
932 // add home alt if needed
933 handle_change_alt_request(cmd);
934
935 // verify we received the command
936 result = MAV_MISSION_ACCEPTED;
937 }
938 send_mission_ack(msg, MAV_MISSION_TYPE_MISSION, result);
939 return;
940 }
941#endif
942
943 // not a guided-mode reqest
944 MissionItemProtocol *prot = gcs().get_prot_for_mission_type(type);
945 if (prot == nullptr) {
946 send_mission_ack(msg, type, MAV_MISSION_UNSUPPORTED);
947 return;
948 }
949
950 if (send_mission_item_warning) {
951 prot->send_mission_item_warning();
952 }
953
954 if (!prot->receiving) {
955 send_mission_ack(msg, type, MAV_MISSION_ERROR);
956 return;
957 }
958
959 prot->handle_mission_item(msg, mission_item_int);
960}

962ap_message GCS_MAVLINK::mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(const uint32_t mavlink_id) const
963{
964 // MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST doesn't correspond to a mavlink message directly.
965 // It is used to request the next waypoint after receiving one.
966
967 // MSG_NEXT_PARAM doesn't correspond to a mavlink message directly.
968 // It is used to send the next parameter in a stream after sending one
969
970 // MSG_NAMED_FLOAT messages can't really be "streamed"...
971
972 static const struct {
973 uint32_t mavlink_id;
974 ap_message msg_id;
975 } map[] {
976 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HEARTBEAT, MSG_HEARTBEAT},

980 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HOME_POSITION, MSG_HOME},
981 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_GPS_GLOBAL_ORIGIN, MSG_ORIGIN},
982 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SYS_STATUS, MSG_SYS_STATUS},
983 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_POWER_STATUS, MSG_POWER_STATUS},
984#if HAL_WITH_MCU_MONITORING
985 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MCU_STATUS, MSG_MCU_STATUS},
986#endif
987 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MEMINFO, MSG_MEMINFO},
988 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_NAV_CONTROLLER_OUTPUT, MSG_NAV_CONTROLLER_OUTPUT},
989 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_CURRENT, MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT},
990 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_VFR_HUD, MSG_VFR_HUD},
991 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SERVO_OUTPUT_RAW, MSG_SERVO_OUTPUT_RAW},
992 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RC_CHANNELS, MSG_RC_CHANNELS},
993 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RC_CHANNELS_RAW, MSG_RC_CHANNELS_RAW},
994 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RAW_IMU, MSG_RAW_IMU},
995 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SCALED_IMU, MSG_SCALED_IMU},
996 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SCALED_IMU2, MSG_SCALED_IMU2},
997 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SCALED_IMU3, MSG_SCALED_IMU3},
998 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SCALED_PRESSURE, MSG_SCALED_PRESSURE},
999 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_SCALED_PRESSURE2, MSG_SCALED_PRESSURE2},

1002 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_GPS_RAW_INT, MSG_GPS_RAW},

1022 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_WIND, MSG_WIND},

1060 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_ATTITUDE_TARGET, MSG_ATTITUDE_TARGET},
1061 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_POSITION_TARGET_GLOBAL_INT, MSG_POSITION_TARGET_GLOBAL_INT},
1062 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_POSITION_TARGET_LOCAL_NED, MSG_POSITION_TARGET_LOCAL_NED},
1063#if HAL_ADSB_ENABLED
1064 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_ADSB_VEHICLE, MSG_ADSB_VEHICLE},
1065#endif
1066#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
1067 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_BATTERY_STATUS, MSG_BATTERY_STATUS},
1068#endif
1069 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_AOA_SSA, MSG_AOA_SSA},
1070#if HAL_LANDING_DEEPSTALL_ENABLED
1071 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_DEEPSTALL, MSG_LANDING},
1072#endif
1073 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_EXTENDED_SYS_STATE, MSG_EXTENDED_SYS_STATE},
1074 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_AUTOPILOT_VERSION, MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION},
1075#if HAL_EFI_ENABLED
1076 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_EFI_STATUS, MSG_EFI_STATUS},
1077#endif
1078#if HAL_GENERATOR_ENABLED
1079 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_GENERATOR_STATUS, MSG_GENERATOR_STATUS},
1080#endif
1081#if AP_WINCH_ENABLED
1082 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_WINCH_STATUS, MSG_WINCH_STATUS},
1083#endif
1084#if HAL_WITH_ESC_TELEM
1085 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_ESC_TELEMETRY_1_TO_4, MSG_ESC_TELEMETRY},
1086#endif
1087#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED && APM_BUILD_TYPE(APM_BUILD_Rover)
1088 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_WATER_DEPTH, MSG_WATER_DEPTH},
1089#endif
1090#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
1091 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HIGH_LATENCY2, MSG_HIGH_LATENCY2},
1092#endif
1093#if AP_AIS_ENABLED
1094 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_AIS_VESSEL, MSG_AIS_VESSEL},
1095#endif
1096#if AP_MAVLINK_MSG_UAVIONIX_ADSB_OUT_STATUS_ENABLED
1097 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_UAVIONIX_ADSB_OUT_STATUS, MSG_UAVIONIX_ADSB_OUT_STATUS},
1098#endif
1099#if AP_MAVLINK_MSG_RELAY_STATUS_ENABLED
1100 { MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RELAY_STATUS, MSG_RELAY_STATUS},
1101#endif
1102 };
1103
1104 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(map); i++) {
1105 if (map[i].mavlink_id == mavlink_id) {
1106 return map[i].msg_id;
1107 }
1108 }
1109 return MSG_LAST;
1110}
1111
1112bool GCS_MAVLINK::set_mavlink_message_id_interval(const uint32_t mavlink_id,
1113 const uint16_t interval_ms)
1114{
1115 const ap_message id = mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(mavlink_id);
1116 if (id == MSG_LAST) {
1117 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "No ap_message for mavlink id (%u)", (unsigned int)mavlink_id);
1118 return false;
1119 }
1120 return set_ap_message_interval(id, interval_ms);
1121}
1122
1123bool GCS_MAVLINK::should_send_message_in_delay_callback(const ap_message id) const
1124{
1125 // No ID we return true for may take more than a few hundred
1126 // microseconds to return!
1127
1128 switch (id) {
1129 case MSG_NEXT_PARAM:
1130 case MSG_HEARTBEAT:
1131#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
1132 case MSG_HIGH_LATENCY2:
1133#endif
1134 case MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION:
1135 return true;
1136 default:
1137 return false;
1138 }
1139
1140 return false;
1141}
1142
1143uint16_t GCS_MAVLINK::get_reschedule_interval_ms(const deferred_message_bucket_t &deferred) const
1144{
1145 uint32_t interval_ms = deferred.interval_ms;
1146
1147 interval_ms += stream_slowdown_ms;
1148
1149 // slow most messages down if we're transfering parameters or
1150 // waypoints:
1151 if (_queued_parameter) {
1152 // we are sending parameters, penalize streams:
1153 interval_ms *= 4;
1154 }
1155 if (requesting_mission_items()) {
1156 // we are sending requests for waypoints, penalize streams:
1157 interval_ms *= 4;
1158 }
1159#if AP_MAVLINK_FTP_ENABLED
1160 if (AP_HAL::millis() - ftp.last_send_ms < 500) {
1161 // we are sending ftp replies
1162 interval_ms *= 4;
1163 }
1164#endif
1165
1166 if (interval_ms > 60000) {
1167 return 60000;
1168 }
1169
1170 return interval_ms;
1171}
1172
1173// typical runtime on fmuv3: 5 microseconds for 3 buckets
1174void GCS_MAVLINK::find_next_bucket_to_send(uint16_t now16_ms)
1175{
1176#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1177 void *data = hal.scheduler->disable_interrupts_save();
1178 uint32_t start_us = AP_HAL::micros();
1179#endif
1180
1181 // all done sending this bucket... find another bucket...
1182 sending_bucket_id = no_bucket_to_send;
1183 uint16_t ms_before_send_next_bucket_to_send = UINT16_MAX;
1184 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message_bucket); i++) {
1185 if (deferred_message_bucket[i].ap_message_ids.count() == 0) {
1186 // no entries
1187 continue;
1188 }
1189 const uint16_t interval = get_reschedule_interval_ms(deferred_message_bucket[i]);
1190 const uint16_t ms_since_last_sent = now16_ms - deferred_message_bucket[i].last_sent_ms;
1191 uint16_t ms_before_send_this_bucket;
1192 if (ms_since_last_sent > interval) {
1193 // should already have sent this bucket!
1194 ms_before_send_this_bucket = 0;
1195 } else {
1196 ms_before_send_this_bucket = interval - ms_since_last_sent;
1197 }
1198 if (ms_before_send_this_bucket < ms_before_send_next_bucket_to_send) {
1199 sending_bucket_id = i;
1200 ms_before_send_next_bucket_to_send = ms_before_send_this_bucket;
1201 }
1202 }
1203 if (sending_bucket_id != no_bucket_to_send) {
1204 bucket_message_ids_to_send = deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id].ap_message_ids;
1205 } else {
1206 bucket_message_ids_to_send.clearall();
1207 }
1208
1209#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1210 uint32_t delta_us = AP_HAL::micros() - start_us;
1211 hal.scheduler->restore_interrupts(data);
1212 if (delta_us > try_send_message_stats.fnbts_maxtime) {
1213 try_send_message_stats.fnbts_maxtime = delta_us;
1214 }
1215#endif
1216}
1217
1218ap_message GCS_MAVLINK::next_deferred_bucket_message_to_send(uint16_t now16_ms)
1219{
1220 if (sending_bucket_id == no_bucket_to_send) {
1221 // could happen if all streamrates are zero?
1222 return no_message_to_send;
1223 }
1224
1225 const uint16_t ms_since_last_sent = now16_ms - deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id].last_sent_ms;
1226 if (ms_since_last_sent < get_reschedule_interval_ms(deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id])) {
1227 // not time to send this bucket
1228 return no_message_to_send;
1229 }
1230
1231 const int16_t next = bucket_message_ids_to_send.first_set();
1232 if (next == -1) {
1233 // should not happen
1234#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
1235 AP_HAL::panic("next_deferred_bucket_message_to_send called on empty bucket");
1236#endif
1237 find_next_bucket_to_send(now16_ms);
1238 return no_message_to_send;
1239 }
1240 return (ap_message)next;
1241}
1242
1243// call try_send_message if appropriate. Incorporates debug code to
1244// record how long it takes to send a message. try_send_message is
1245// expected to be overridden, not this function.
1246bool GCS_MAVLINK::do_try_send_message(const ap_message id)
1247{
1248 const bool in_delay_callback = hal.scheduler->in_delay_callback();
1249 if (in_delay_callback && !should_send_message_in_delay_callback(id)) {
1250 return true;
1251 }
1252 if (telemetry_delayed()) {
1253 return false;
1254 }
1255 WITH_SEMAPHORE(comm_chan_lock(chan));
1256#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1257 void *data = hal.scheduler->disable_interrupts_save();
1258 uint32_t start_send_message_us = AP_HAL::micros();
1259#endif
1260 if (!try_send_message(id)) {
1261 // didn't fit in buffer...
1262#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1263 try_send_message_stats.no_space_for_message++;
1264 hal.scheduler->restore_interrupts(data);
1265#endif
1266 return false;
1267 }
1268#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1269 const uint32_t delta_us = AP_HAL::micros() - start_send_message_us;
1270 hal.scheduler->restore_interrupts(data);
1271 if (delta_us > try_send_message_stats.longest_time_us) {
1272 try_send_message_stats.longest_time_us = delta_us;
1273 try_send_message_stats.longest_id = id;
1274 }
1275#endif
1276 return true;
1277}
1278
1279int8_t GCS_MAVLINK::get_deferred_message_index(const ap_message id) const
1280{
1281 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message); i++) {
1282 if (deferred_message[i].id == id) {
1283 return i;
1284 }
1285 }
1286 return -1;
1287}
1288
1289int8_t GCS_MAVLINK::deferred_message_to_send_index(uint16_t now16_ms)
1290{
1291
1292 if (next_deferred_message_to_send_cache == -1) {
1293 uint16_t ms_before_next_message_to_send = UINT16_MAX;
1294 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message); i++) {
1295 const uint16_t interval_ms = deferred_message[i].interval_ms;
1296 if (interval_ms == 0) {
1297 continue;
1298 }
1299 const uint16_t ms_since_last_sent = now16_ms - deferred_message[i].last_sent_ms;
1300 uint16_t ms_before_send_this_message;
1301 if (ms_since_last_sent > interval_ms) {
1302 // should already have sent this one!
1303 ms_before_send_this_message = 0;
1304#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1305 try_send_message_stats.behind++;
1306#endif
1307 } else {
1308 ms_before_send_this_message = interval_ms - ms_since_last_sent;
1309 }
1310 if (ms_before_send_this_message < ms_before_next_message_to_send) {
1311 next_deferred_message_to_send_cache = i;
1312 ms_before_next_message_to_send = ms_before_send_this_message;
1313 }
1314 }
1315 }
1316
1317 if (next_deferred_message_to_send_cache == -1) {
1318 // this really shouldn't happen; we force parameter rates, for example.
1319 return -1;
1320 }
1321
1322 const uint16_t ms_since_last_sent = now16_ms - deferred_message[next_deferred_message_to_send_cache].last_sent_ms;
1323 if (ms_since_last_sent < deferred_message[next_deferred_message_to_send_cache].interval_ms) {
1324 return -1;
1325 }
1326
1327 return next_deferred_message_to_send_cache;
1328}
1329
1330bool GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::send_ack(MAV_RESULT result)
1331{
1332 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, COMMAND_ACK)) {
1333 // can't fit the ACK, come back to this later
1334 return false;
1335 }
1336
1337 mavlink_msg_command_ack_send(
1338 chan,
1339 mav_cmd,
1340 result,
1341 0,
1342 0,
1343 requesting_sysid,
1344 requesting_compid
1345 );
1346
1347 return true;
1348}
1349
1350bool GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::send_in_progress()
1351{
1352 return send_ack(MAV_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS);
1353}
1354
1355bool GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::conclude(MAV_RESULT result)
1356{
1357 if (!send_ack(result)) {
1358 return false;
1359 }
1360 task = Type::NONE;
1361 return true;
1362}
1363
1364GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress *GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::get_task(MAV_CMD mav_cmd, GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::Type t, uint8_t sysid, uint8_t compid, mavlink_channel_t chan)
1365{
1366 // we can't have two outstanding tasks for the same command from
1367 // the same mavlink node or the result is ambiguous:
1368 for (auto &_task : in_progress_tasks) {
1369 if (_task.task == Type::NONE) {
1370 continue;
1371 }
1372 if (_task.mav_cmd == mav_cmd &&
1373 _task.requesting_sysid == sysid &&
1374 _task.requesting_compid == compid) {
1375 return nullptr;
1376 }
1377 }
1378
1379 for (auto &_task : in_progress_tasks) {
1380 if (_task.task != Type::NONE) {
1381 continue;
1382 }
1383 _task.chan = chan;
1384 _task.task = t;
1385 _task.mav_cmd = mav_cmd;
1386 _task.requesting_sysid = sysid;
1387 _task.requesting_compid = compid;
1388 return &_task;
1389 }
1390 return nullptr;
1391}
1392
1393
1394void GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::check_tasks()
1395{
1396 // run these checks only intermittently (rate-limits the
1397 // MAV_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS messages):
1398 const uint32_t now_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
1399 if (now_ms - last_check_ms < 1000) {
1400 return;
1401 }
1402 last_check_ms = now_ms;
1403
1404 for (auto &task : in_progress_tasks) {
1405 switch (task.task) {
1406 case Type::NONE:
1407 break;
1408 case Type::AIRSPEED_CAL: {
1409#if AP_AIRSPEED_ENABLED
1410 const AP_Airspeed *airspeed = AP_Airspeed::get_singleton();
1411 switch (airspeed->get_calibration_state()) {
1412 case AP_Airspeed::CalibrationState::NOT_STARTED:
1413 // we shouldn't get here
1414 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_FAILED);
1415 break;
1416 case AP_Airspeed::CalibrationState::IN_PROGRESS:
1417 task.send_in_progress();
1418 break;
1419 case AP_Airspeed::CalibrationState::FAILED:
1420 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_FAILED);
1421 break;
1422 case AP_Airspeed::CalibrationState::SUCCESS:
1423 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED);
1424 break;
1425 }
1426#endif
1427 }
1428 break;
1429 case Type::SD_FORMAT:
1430#if AP_FILESYSTEM_FORMAT_ENABLED
1431 switch (AP::FS().get_format_status()) {
1432 case AP_Filesystem_Backend::FormatStatus::NOT_STARTED:
1433 // we shouldn't get here
1434 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_FAILED);
1435 break;
1436 case AP_Filesystem_Backend::FormatStatus::IN_PROGRESS:
1437 case AP_Filesystem_Backend::FormatStatus::PENDING:
1438 task.send_in_progress();
1439 break;
1440 case AP_Filesystem_Backend::FormatStatus::SUCCESS:
1441 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED);
1442 break;
1443 case AP_Filesystem_Backend::FormatStatus::FAILURE:
1444 task.conclude(MAV_RESULT_FAILED);
1445 break;
1446 }
1447#endif
1448 break;
1449 }
1450 }
1451}
1452
1453void GCS_MAVLINK::update_send()
1454{
1455#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
1456 if (!hal.scheduler->in_delay_callback()) {
1457 // AP_Logger will not send log data if we are armed.
1458 AP::logger().handle_log_send();
1459 }
1460#endif
1461 if (!deferred_messages_initialised) {
1462 initialise_message_intervals_from_streamrates();
1463#if HAL_MAVLINK_INTERVALS_FROM_FILES_ENABLED
1464 initialise_message_intervals_from_config_files();
1465#endif
1466 deferred_messages_initialised = true;
1467 }
1468
1469#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1470 uint32_t retry_deferred_body_start = AP_HAL::micros();
1471#endif
1472
1473 // check for any in-progress tasks; check_tasks does its own rate-limiting
1474 GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::check_tasks();
1475
1476 const uint32_t start = AP_HAL::millis();
1477 const uint16_t start16 = start & 0xFFFF;
1478 while (AP_HAL::millis() - start < 5) { // spend a max of 5ms sending messages. This should never trigger - out_of_time() should become true
1479 if (gcs().out_of_time()) {
1480#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1481 try_send_message_stats.out_of_time++;
1482#endif
1483 break;
1484 }
1485
1486#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1487 retry_deferred_body_start = AP_HAL::micros();
1488#endif
1489
1490 // check if any "specially handled" messages should be sent out
1491 {
1492 const int8_t next = deferred_message_to_send_index(start16);
1493 if (next != -1) {
1494 if (!do_try_send_message(deferred_message[next].id)) {
1495 break;
1496 }
1497 // we try to keep output on a regular clock to avoid
1498 // user support questions:
1499 const uint16_t interval_ms = deferred_message[next].interval_ms;
1500 deferred_message[next].last_sent_ms += interval_ms;
1501 // but we do not want to try to catch up too much:
1502 if (uint16_t(start16 - deferred_message[next].last_sent_ms) > interval_ms) {
1503 deferred_message[next].last_sent_ms = start16;
1504 }
1505
1506 next_deferred_message_to_send_cache = -1; // deferred_message_to_send will recalculate
1507#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1508 const uint32_t stop = AP_HAL::micros();
1509 const uint32_t delta = stop - retry_deferred_body_start;
1510 if (delta > try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us) {
1511 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us = delta;
1512 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_type = 1;
1513 }
1514#endif
1515 continue;
1516 }
1517 }
1518
1519 // check for any messages that the code has explicitly sent
1520 const int16_t fs = pushed_ap_message_ids.first_set();
1521 if (fs != -1) {
1522 ap_message next = (ap_message)fs;
1523 if (!do_try_send_message(next)) {
1524 break;
1525 }
1526 pushed_ap_message_ids.clear(next);
1527#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1528 const uint32_t stop = AP_HAL::micros();
1529 const uint32_t delta = stop - retry_deferred_body_start;
1530 if (delta > try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us) {
1531 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us = delta;
1532 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_type = 2;
1533 }
1534#endif
1535 continue;
1536 }
1537
1538 ap_message next = next_deferred_bucket_message_to_send(start16);
1539 if (next != no_message_to_send) {
1540 if (!do_try_send_message(next)) {
1541 break;
1542 }
1543 bucket_message_ids_to_send.clear(next);
1544 if (bucket_message_ids_to_send.count() == 0) {
1545 // we sent everything in the bucket. Reschedule it.
1546 // we try to keep output on a regular clock to avoid
1547 // user support questions:
1548 const uint16_t interval_ms = get_reschedule_interval_ms(deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id]);
1549 deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id].last_sent_ms += interval_ms;
1550 // but we do not want to try to catch up too much:
1551 if (uint16_t(start16 - deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id].last_sent_ms) > interval_ms) {
1552 deferred_message_bucket[sending_bucket_id].last_sent_ms = start16;
1553 }
1554 find_next_bucket_to_send(start16);
1555 }
1556#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1557 const uint32_t stop = AP_HAL::micros();
1558 const uint32_t delta = stop - retry_deferred_body_start;
1559 if (delta > try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us) {
1560 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us = delta;
1561 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_type = 3;
1562 }
1563#endif
1564 continue;
1565 }
1566 break;
1567 }
1568#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1569 const uint32_t stop = AP_HAL::micros();
1570 const uint32_t delta = stop - retry_deferred_body_start;
1571 if (delta > try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us) {
1572 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us = delta;
1573 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_type = 4;
1574 }
1575#endif
1576
1577 // update the number of packets transmitted base on seqno, making
1578 // the assumption that we don't send more than 256 messages
1579 // between the last pass through here
1580 send_packet_count += uint8_t(_channel_status.current_tx_seq - last_tx_seq);
1581 last_tx_seq = _channel_status.current_tx_seq;
1582}
1583
1584void GCS_MAVLINK::remove_message_from_bucket(int8_t bucket, ap_message id)
1585{
1586 deferred_message_bucket[bucket].ap_message_ids.clear(id);
1587 if (deferred_message_bucket[bucket].ap_message_ids.count() == 0) {
1588 // bucket empty. Free it:
1589 deferred_message_bucket[bucket].interval_ms = 0;
1590 deferred_message_bucket[bucket].last_sent_ms = 0;
1591 }
1592
1593 if (bucket == sending_bucket_id) {
1594 bucket_message_ids_to_send.clear(id);
1595 if (bucket_message_ids_to_send.count() == 0) {
1596 find_next_bucket_to_send(AP_HAL::millis16());
1597 } else {
1598#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
1599 if (deferred_message_bucket[bucket].interval_ms == 0 &&
1600 deferred_message_bucket[bucket].last_sent_ms == 0) {
1601 // we just freed this bucket! this would mean that
1602 // somehow our messages-still-to-send was a superset
1603 // of the messages in the bucket we were sending,
1604 // which would be bad.
1605 INTERNAL_ERROR(AP_InternalError::error_t::flow_of_control);
1606 }
1607#endif
1608 }
1609 }
1610}
1611
1612bool GCS_MAVLINK::set_ap_message_interval(enum ap_message id, uint16_t interval_ms)
1613{
1614 if (id == MSG_NEXT_PARAM) {
1615 // force parameters to *always* get streamed so a vehicle is
1616 // recoverable from bad configuration:
1617 if (interval_ms == 0) {
1618 interval_ms = 100;
1619 } else if (interval_ms > 1000) {
1620 interval_ms = 1000;
1621 }
1622 }
1623
1624#if AP_SCHEDULER_ENABLED
1625 // send messages out at most 80% of main loop rate
1626 if (interval_ms != 0 &&
1627 interval_ms*800 < AP::scheduler().get_loop_period_us()) {
1628 interval_ms = AP::scheduler().get_loop_period_us()/800.0f;
1629 }
1630#endif
1631
1632 // check if it's a specially-handled message:
1633 const int8_t deferred_offset = get_deferred_message_index(id);
1634 if (deferred_offset != -1) {
1635 deferred_message[deferred_offset].interval_ms = interval_ms;
1636 deferred_message[deferred_offset].last_sent_ms = AP_HAL::millis16();
1637 return true;
1638 }
1639
1640 // see which bucket has the closest interval:
1641 int8_t closest_bucket = -1;
1642 uint16_t closest_bucket_interval_delta = UINT16_MAX;
1643 int8_t in_bucket = -1;
1644 int8_t empty_bucket_id = -1;
1645 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message_bucket); i++) {
1646 const deferred_message_bucket_t &bucket = deferred_message_bucket[i];
1647 if (bucket.interval_ms == 0) {
1648 // unused bucket
1649 if (empty_bucket_id == -1) {
1650 empty_bucket_id = i;
1651 }
1652#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
1653 if (bucket.ap_message_ids.count() != 0) {
1654 AP_HAL::panic("Bucket %u has zero interval but with ids set", i);
1655 }
1656#endif
1657 continue;
1658 }
1659 if (bucket.ap_message_ids.get(id)) {
1660 in_bucket = i;
1661 }
1662 const uint16_t interval_delta = abs(bucket.interval_ms - interval_ms);
1663 if (interval_delta < closest_bucket_interval_delta) {
1664 closest_bucket = i;
1665 closest_bucket_interval_delta = interval_delta;
1666 }
1667 }
1668
1669 if (in_bucket == -1 && interval_ms == 0) {
1670 // not in a bucket and told to remove from scheduling
1671 return true;
1672 }
1673
1674 if (in_bucket != -1) {
1675 if (interval_ms == 0) {
1676 // remove it
1677 remove_message_from_bucket(in_bucket, id);
1678 return true;
1679 }
1680 if (closest_bucket_interval_delta == 0 &&
1681 in_bucket == closest_bucket) {
1682 // don't need to move it
1683 return true;
1684 }
1685 // remove from existing bucket
1686 remove_message_from_bucket(in_bucket, id);
1687 if (empty_bucket_id == -1 &&
1688 deferred_message_bucket[in_bucket].ap_message_ids.count() == 0) {
1689 empty_bucket_id = in_bucket;
1690 }
1691 }
1692
1693 if (closest_bucket == -1 && empty_bucket_id == -1) {
1694 // gah?!
1695#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
1696 ::fprintf(stderr, "no buckets?!\n");
1697 abort();
1698#endif
1699 return false;
1700 }
1701
1702 if (closest_bucket_interval_delta != 0 &&
1703 empty_bucket_id != -1) {
1704 // allocate a bucket for this interval
1705 deferred_message_bucket[empty_bucket_id].interval_ms = interval_ms;
1706 deferred_message_bucket[empty_bucket_id].last_sent_ms = AP_HAL::millis16();
1707 closest_bucket = empty_bucket_id;
1708 }
1709
1710 deferred_message_bucket[closest_bucket].ap_message_ids.set(id);
1711
1712 if (sending_bucket_id == no_bucket_to_send) {
1713 sending_bucket_id = closest_bucket;
1714 bucket_message_ids_to_send = deferred_message_bucket[closest_bucket].ap_message_ids;
1715 }
1716
1717 return true;
1718}
1719
1720// queue a message to be sent (try_send_message does the *actual*
1721// mavlink work!)
1722void GCS_MAVLINK::send_message(enum ap_message id)
1723{
1724 switch (id) {
1725 case MSG_HEARTBEAT:
1726#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
1727 case MSG_HIGH_LATENCY2:
1728#endif
1729 save_signing_timestamp(false);
1730 // update the mask of all streaming channels
1731 if (is_streaming()) {
1732 GCS_MAVLINK::chan_is_streaming |= (1U<<(chan-MAVLINK_COMM_0));
1733 } else {
1734 GCS_MAVLINK::chan_is_streaming &= ~(1U<<(chan-MAVLINK_COMM_0));
1735 }
1736 break;
1737 default:
1738 break;
1739 }
1740
1741 pushed_ap_message_ids.set(id);
1742}
1743
1744void GCS_MAVLINK::packetReceived(const mavlink_status_t &status,
1745 const mavlink_message_t &msg)
1746{
1747 // we exclude radio packets because we historically used this to
1748 // make it possible to use the CLI over the radio
1749 if (msg.msgid != MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RADIO && msg.msgid != MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RADIO_STATUS) {
1750 mavlink_active |= (1U<<(chan-MAVLINK_COMM_0));
1751 }
1752 const auto mavlink_protocol = uartstate->get_protocol();
1753 if (!(status.flags & MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_IN_MAVLINK1) &&
1754 (status.flags & MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1) &&
1755 (mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink2 ||
1756 mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLinkHL)) {
1757 // if we receive any MAVLink2 packets on a connection
1758 // currently sending MAVLink1 then switch to sending
1759 // MAVLink2
1760 _channel_status.flags &= ~MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1;
1761 }
1762 if (!routing.check_and_forward(*this, msg)) {
1763 // the routing code has indicated we should not handle this packet locally
1764 return;
1765 }
1766 if (msg.msgid == MAVLINK_MSG_ID_GLOBAL_POSITION_INT) {
1767#if HAL_MOUNT_ENABLED
1768 // allow mounts to see the location of other vehicles
1769 handle_mount_message(msg);
1770#endif
1771 }
1772#if AP_SCRIPTING_ENABLED
1773 {
1774 AP_Scripting *scripting = AP_Scripting::get_singleton();
1775 if (scripting != nullptr) {
1776 scripting->handle_message(msg, chan);
1777 }
1778 }
1779#endif // AP_SCRIPTING_ENABLED
1780 if (!accept_packet(status, msg)) {
1781 // e.g. enforce-sysid says we shouldn't look at this packet
1782 return;
1783 }
1784 handle_message(msg);
1785}
1786
1787void
1788GCS_MAVLINK::update_receive(uint32_t max_time_us)
1789{
1790 // do absolutely nothing if we are locked
1791 if (locked()) {
1792 return;
1793 }
1794
1795 // receive new packets
1796 mavlink_message_t msg;
1797 mavlink_status_t status;
1798 uint32_t tstart_us = AP_HAL::micros();
1799 uint32_t now_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
1800
1801 status.packet_rx_drop_count = 0;
1802
1803 const uint16_t nbytes = _port->available();
1804 for (uint16_t i=0; i<nbytes; i++)
1805 {
1806 const uint8_t c = (uint8_t)_port->read();
1807 const uint32_t protocol_timeout = 4000;
1808
1809 if (alternative.handler &&
1810 now_ms - alternative.last_mavlink_ms > protocol_timeout) {
1811 /*
1812 we have an alternative protocol handler installed and we
1813 haven't parsed a MAVLink packet for 4 seconds. Try
1814 parsing using alternative handler
1815 */
1816 if (alternative.handler(c, mavlink_comm_port[chan])) {
1817 alternative.last_alternate_ms = now_ms;
1818 gcs_alternative_active[chan] = true;
1819 }
1820
1821 /*
1822 we may also try parsing as MAVLink if we haven't had a
1823 successful parse on the alternative protocol for 4s
1824 */
1825 if (now_ms - alternative.last_alternate_ms <= protocol_timeout) {
1826 continue;
1827 }
1828 }
1829
1830 bool parsed_packet = false;
1831
1832 // Try to get a new message
1833 if (mavlink_frame_char_buffer(channel_buffer(), channel_status(), c, &msg, &status) == MAVLINK_FRAMING_OK) {
1834 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_msgid = msg.msgid;
1835 packetReceived(status, msg);
1836 parsed_packet = true;
1837 gcs_alternative_active[chan] = false;
1838 alternative.last_mavlink_ms = now_ms;
1839 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_msgid = 0;
1840 }
1841
1842 if (parsed_packet || i % 100 == 0) {
1843 // make sure we don't spend too much time parsing mavlink messages
1844 if (AP_HAL::micros() - tstart_us > max_time_us) {
1845 break;
1846 }
1847 }
1848 }
1849
1850 const uint32_t tnow = AP_HAL::millis();
1851
1852 // send a timesync message every 10 seconds; this is for data
1853 // collection purposes
1854 if (tnow - _timesync_request.last_sent_ms > _timesync_request.interval_ms && !is_private()) {
1855 if (HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, TIMESYNC)) {
1856 send_timesync();
1857 _timesync_request.last_sent_ms = tnow;
1858 }
1859 }
1860
1861#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
1862 // consider logging mavlink stats:
1863 if (is_active() || is_streaming()) {
1864 if (tnow - last_mavlink_stats_logged > 1000) {
1865 log_mavlink_stats();
1866 last_mavlink_stats_logged = tnow;
1867 }
1868 }
1869#endif
1870
1871#if GCS_DEBUG_SEND_MESSAGE_TIMINGS
1872
1873 const uint16_t now16_ms{AP_HAL::millis16()};
1874
1875 if (uint16_t(now16_ms - try_send_message_stats.statustext_last_sent_ms) > 10000U) {
1876 if (try_send_message_stats.longest_time_us) {
1877 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1878 "GCS.chan(%u): ap_msg=%u took %uus to send",
1879 chan,
1880 try_send_message_stats.longest_id,
1881 try_send_message_stats.longest_time_us);
1882 try_send_message_stats.longest_time_us = 0;
1883 }
1884 if (try_send_message_stats.no_space_for_message &&
1885 (is_active() || is_streaming())) {
1886 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1887 "GCS.chan(%u): out-of-space: %u",
1888 chan,
1889 try_send_message_stats.no_space_for_message);
1890 try_send_message_stats.no_space_for_message = 0;
1891 }
1892 if (try_send_message_stats.out_of_time) {
1893 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1894 "GCS.chan(%u): out-of-time=%u",
1895 chan,
1896 try_send_message_stats.out_of_time);
1897 try_send_message_stats.out_of_time = 0;
1898 }
1899 if (max_slowdown_ms) {
1900 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1901 "GCS.chan(%u): max slowdown=%u",
1902 chan,
1903 max_slowdown_ms);
1904 max_slowdown_ms = 0;
1905 }
1906 if (try_send_message_stats.behind) {
1907 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1908 "GCS.chan(%u): behind=%u",
1909 chan,
1910 try_send_message_stats.behind);
1911 try_send_message_stats.behind = 0;
1912 }
1913 if (try_send_message_stats.fnbts_maxtime) {
1914 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1915 "GCS.chan(%u): fnbts_maxtime=%uus",
1916 chan,
1917 try_send_message_stats.fnbts_maxtime);
1918 try_send_message_stats.fnbts_maxtime = 0;
1919 }
1920 if (try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us) {
1921 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1922 "GCS.chan(%u): retry_body_maxtime=%uus (%u)",
1923 chan,
1924 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us,
1925 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_type
1926 );
1927 try_send_message_stats.max_retry_deferred_body_us = 0;
1928 }
1929
1930 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message_bucket); i++) {
1931 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
1932 "B. intvl. (%u): %u %u %u %u %u",
1933 chan,
1934 deferred_message_bucket[0].interval_ms,
1935 deferred_message_bucket[1].interval_ms,
1936 deferred_message_bucket[2].interval_ms,
1937 deferred_message_bucket[3].interval_ms,
1938 deferred_message_bucket[4].interval_ms);
1939 }
1940
1941 try_send_message_stats.statustext_last_sent_ms = now16_ms;
1942 }
1943#endif
1944}

1946#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
1947/*
1948 record stats about this link to logger
1949*/
1950void GCS_MAVLINK::log_mavlink_stats()
1951{
1952 uint8_t flags = 0;
1953 if (signing_enabled()) {
1954 flags |= (uint8_t)Flags::USING_SIGNING;
1955 }
1956 if (is_streaming()) {
1957 flags |= (uint8_t)Flags::STREAMING;
1958 }
1959 if (is_active()) {
1960 flags |= (uint8_t)Flags::ACTIVE;
1961 }
1962 if (is_private()) {
1963 flags |= (uint8_t)Flags::PRIVATE;
1964 }
1965 if (locked()) {
1966 flags |= (uint8_t)Flags::LOCKED;
1967 }
1968
1969 const struct log_MAV pkt{
1970 LOG_PACKET_HEADER_INIT(LOG_MAV_MSG),
1971 time_us : AP_HAL::micros64(),
1972 chan : (uint8_t)chan,
1973 packet_tx_count : send_packet_count,
1974 packet_rx_success_count: _channel_status.packet_rx_success_count,
1975 packet_rx_drop_count : _channel_status.packet_rx_drop_count,
1976 flags : flags,
1977 stream_slowdown_ms : stream_slowdown_ms,
1978 times_full : out_of_space_to_send_count,
1979 };
1980
1981 AP::logger().WriteBlock(&pkt, sizeof(pkt));
1982}
1983#endif

1998 AP_HAL::millis());
1999}

2110void GCS_MAVLINK::send_scaled_imu(uint8_t instance, void (*send_fn)(mavlink_channel_t chan, uint32_t time_ms, int16_t xacc, int16_t yacc, int16_t zacc, int16_t xgyro, int16_t ygyro, int16_t zgyro, int16_t xmag, int16_t ymag, int16_t zmag, int16_t temperature))
2111{

2115
2116 bool have_data = false;
2117 Vector3f accel{};
2118 if (ins.get_accel_count() > instance) {
2119 accel = ins.get_accel(instance);
2120 _temperature = ins.get_temperature(instance)*100;
2121 have_data = true;
2122 }
2123 Vector3f gyro{};
2124 if (ins.get_gyro_count() > instance) {
2125 gyro = ins.get_gyro(instance);
2126 have_data = true;
2127 }
2128 Vector3f mag;
2129#if AP_COMPASS_ENABLED
2130 const Compass &compass = AP::compass();
2131 if (compass.get_count() > instance) {
2132 mag = compass.get_field(instance);
2133 have_data = true;
2134 }
2135#endif
2136 if (!have_data) {
2137 return;
2138 }
2139 send_fn(
2140 chan,
2141 AP_HAL::millis(),
2142 accel.x * 1000.0f / GRAVITY_MSS,
2143 accel.y * 1000.0f / GRAVITY_MSS,
2144 accel.z * 1000.0f / GRAVITY_MSS,
2145 gyro.x * 1000.0f,
2146 gyro.y * 1000.0f,
2147 gyro.z * 1000.0f,
2148 mag.x,
2149 mag.y,
2150 mag.z,
2151 _temperature);
2152#endif
2153}

2156// send data for barometer and airspeed sensors instances. In the
2157// case that we run out of instances of one before the other we send
2158// the relevant fields as 0.
2159void GCS_MAVLINK::send_scaled_pressure_instance(uint8_t instance, void (*send_fn)(mavlink_channel_t chan, uint32_t time_boot_ms, float press_abs, float press_diff, int16_t temperature, int16_t temperature_press_diff))
2160{
2161 const AP_Baro &barometer = AP::baro();
2162
2163 bool have_data = false;
2164
2165 float press_abs = 0.0f;
2166 int16_t temperature = 0; // Absolute pressure temperature
2167 int16_t temperature_press_diff = 0; // Differential pressure temperature
2168 if (instance < barometer.num_instances()) {
2169 press_abs = barometer.get_pressure(instance) * 0.01f;
2170 temperature = barometer.get_temperature(instance)*100;
2171 have_data = true;
2172 }
2173
2174 float press_diff = 0; // pascal
2175#if AP_AIRSPEED_ENABLED
2176 AP_Airspeed *airspeed = AP_Airspeed::get_singleton();
2177 if (airspeed != nullptr &&
2178 airspeed->enabled(instance)) {
2179 press_diff = airspeed->get_differential_pressure(instance) * 0.01f;
2180 float temp;
2181 if (airspeed->get_temperature(instance,temp)) {
2182 temperature_press_diff = temp * 100;
2183 if (temperature_press_diff == 0) {
2184 // don't send zero as that is the value for 'no data'
2185 temperature_press_diff = 1;
2186 }
2187 }
2188 have_data = true;
2189 }
2190#endif
2191
2192 if (!have_data) {
2193 return;
2194 }
2195
2196 send_fn(
2197 chan,
2198 AP_HAL::millis(),
2199 press_abs, // hectopascal
2200 press_diff, // hectopascal
2201 temperature, // 0.01 degrees C
2202 temperature_press_diff); // 0.01 degrees C
2203}
2204
2205void GCS_MAVLINK::send_scaled_pressure()
2206{
2207 send_scaled_pressure_instance(0, mavlink_msg_scaled_pressure_send);
2208}
2209
2210void GCS_MAVLINK::send_scaled_pressure2()
2211{
2212 send_scaled_pressure_instance(1, mavlink_msg_scaled_pressure2_send);
2213}
2214
2215void GCS_MAVLINK::send_scaled_pressure3()
2216{
2217 send_scaled_pressure_instance(2, mavlink_msg_scaled_pressure3_send);
2218}

2236
2237/*
2238 send a statustext text string to specific MAVLink bitmask
2239*/
2240void GCS::send_textv(MAV_SEVERITY severity, const char *fmt, va_list arg_list, uint8_t dest_bitmask)
2241{
2242 char first_piece_of_text[MAVLINK_MSG_STATUSTEXT_FIELD_TEXT_LEN+1]{};
2243
2244 do {
2245 // send_text can be called from multiple threads; we must
2246 // protect the "text" member with _statustext_sem
2247 WITH_SEMAPHORE(_statustext_queue.semaphore());
2248 hal.util->vsnprintf(statustext_printf_buffer, sizeof(statustext_printf_buffer), fmt, arg_list);
2249 memcpy(first_piece_of_text, statustext_printf_buffer, ARRAY_SIZE(first_piece_of_text)-1);
2250
2251 // filter destination ports to only allow active ports.
2252 statustext_t statustext{};
2253 if (update_send_has_been_called) {
2254 statustext.bitmask = statustext_send_channel_mask();
2255 } else {
2256 // we have not yet initialised the streaming-channel-mask,
2257 // which is done as part of the update() call. So just send
2258 // it to all channels:
2259 statustext.bitmask = (1<<_num_gcs)-1;
2260 }
2261 statustext.bitmask &= dest_bitmask;
2262 if (!statustext.bitmask) {
2263 // nowhere to send
2264 break;
2265 }
2266
2267 statustext.entry_created_ms = AP_HAL::millis16();
2268 statustext.msg.severity = severity;
2269
2270 static uint16_t msgid;
2271 if (strlen(statustext_printf_buffer) > sizeof(statustext.msg.text)) {
2272 msgid++;
2273 if (msgid == 0) {
2274 msgid = 1;
2275 }
2276 statustext.msg.id = msgid;
2277 }
2278
2279 const char *remainder = statustext_printf_buffer;
2280 for (uint8_t i=0; i<_status_capacity; i++) {
2281 statustext.msg.chunk_seq = i;
2282 const size_t remainder_len = strlen(remainder);
2283 // note that remainder_len may be zero here!
2284 uint16_t n = MIN(sizeof(statustext.msg.text), remainder_len);
2285 if (i == _status_capacity -1 && n == sizeof(statustext.msg.text)) {
2286 // fantastic. This us a very long statustext and
2287 // we've actually managed to push everything else out
2288 // of the queue - this is the last chunk, so we MUST
2289 // null-terminate.
2290 n -= 1;
2291 }
2292 memset(statustext.msg.text, '\0', sizeof(statustext.msg.text));
2293 memcpy(statustext.msg.text, remainder, n);
2294 // The force push will ensure comm links do not block other comm links forever if they fail.
2295 // If we push to a full buffer then we overwrite the oldest entry, effectively removing the
2296 // block but not until the buffer fills up.
2297 _statustext_queue.push_force(statustext);
2298 remainder = &remainder[n];
2299
2300 // note that remainder_len here is the remainder length for
2301 // the *old* remainder!
2302 if (remainder_len < sizeof(statustext.msg.text) || statustext.msg.id == 0) {
2303 break;
2304 }
2305 }
2306 } while (false);
2307
2308#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
2309 // given we don't really know what these methods get up to, we
2310 // don't hold the statustext semaphore while doing them:
2311 AP_Logger *logger = AP_Logger::get_singleton();
2312 if (logger != nullptr) {
2313 logger->Write_Message(first_piece_of_text);
2314 }
2315#endif
2316
2317#if AP_FRSKY_TELEM_ENABLED
2318 frsky = AP::frsky_telem();
2319 if (frsky != nullptr) {
2320 frsky->queue_message(severity, first_piece_of_text);
2321 }
2322#endif
2323#if HAL_SPEKTRUM_TELEM_ENABLED
2324 AP_Spektrum_Telem* spektrum = AP::spektrum_telem();
2325 if (spektrum != nullptr) {
2326 spektrum->queue_message(severity, first_piece_of_text);
2327 }
2328#endif
2329#if HAL_CRSF_TELEM_ENABLED
2330 AP_CRSF_Telem* crsf = AP::crsf_telem();
2331 if (crsf != nullptr) {
2332 crsf->queue_message(severity, first_piece_of_text);
2333 }
2334#endif
2335 AP_Notify *notify = AP_Notify::get_singleton();
2336 if (notify) {
2337 notify->send_text(first_piece_of_text);
2338 }
2339
2340 // push the messages out straight away until the vehicle states
2341 // that it is initialised. At that point we can assume
2342 // update_send is being called
2343 if (!vehicle_initialised()) {
2344 service_statustext();
2345 }
2346}
2347
2348void GCS::service_statustext(void)
2349{
2350 WITH_SEMAPHORE(_statustext_queue.semaphore());
2351
2352 if (_statustext_queue.is_empty()) {
2353 // nothing to do
2354 return;
2355 }
2356
2357 for (uint8_t i=first_backend_to_send; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2358 chan(i)->service_statustext();
2359 }
2360 for (uint8_t i=0; i<first_backend_to_send; i++) {
2361 chan(i)->service_statustext();
2362 }
2363
2364 _statustext_queue.prune();
2365}
2366
2367void GCS::StatusTextQueue::prune(void)
2368{
2369 // consider pruning the statustext queue of ancient entries
2370 const uint32_t now_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
2371 if (now_ms - last_prune_ms < 1000) {
2372 return;
2373 }
2374 last_prune_ms = now_ms;
2375
2376 const uint16_t now16_ms = AP_HAL::millis16();
2377 for (uint8_t idx=0; idx<available(); ) {
2378 const GCS::statustext_t *statustext = (*this)[idx];
2379 if (statustext == nullptr) {
2380 INTERNAL_ERROR(AP_InternalError::error_t::flow_of_control);
2381 break;
2382 }
2383 // be wary of integer promotion here
2384 const uint16_t age = now16_ms - statustext->entry_created_ms;
2385 if (age > 5000) {
2386 // too old. Purge it.
2387 remove(idx);
2388 continue;
2389 }
2390 // this is a queue. If this one wasn't too old then the next
2391 // one isn't either.
2392 break;
2393 }
2394}
2395
2396/*
2397 send a statustext message to specific MAVLink connections in a bitmask
2398
2399 must be called with semaphore held
2400 */
2401void GCS_MAVLINK::service_statustext(void)
2402{
2403 GCS::StatusTextQueue &_statustext_queue = gcs().statustext_queue();
2404
2405 const uint8_t chan_bit = (1U<<chan);
2406 // note the lack of idx++ here. We may remove the iteration item
2407 // from the queue as the last thing we do, in which case we don't
2408 // want to move idx.
2409 const uint16_t payload_size = PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, STATUSTEXT);
2410 for (uint8_t idx=0; idx<_statustext_queue.available(); ) {
2411 WITH_SEMAPHORE(comm_chan_lock(chan));
2412
2413 if (txspace() < payload_size) {
2414 break;
2415 }
2416 GCS::statustext_t *statustext = _statustext_queue[idx];
2417 if (statustext == nullptr) {
2418 INTERNAL_ERROR(AP_InternalError::error_t::flow_of_control);
2419 break;
2420 }
2421
2422 // check to see if we need to send this queue entry:
2423 if (statustext->bitmask & chan_bit) {
2424 mavlink_msg_statustext_send(chan,
2425 statustext->msg.severity,
2426 statustext->msg.text,
2427 statustext->msg.id,
2428 statustext->msg.chunk_seq);
2429 // indicate we've sent the message:
2430 statustext->bitmask &= ~chan_bit;
2431
2432 if (statustext->bitmask == 0) {
2433 // sent everywhere it needs to be sent, remove it from the
2434 // queue but leave idx as-is as we want to handle the
2435 // remaining items which have been bumped up to out
2436 // current index
2437 _statustext_queue.remove(idx);
2438 continue;
2439 }
2440 }
2441 // this item still has places to go. Continue to iterate over the queue
2442 idx++;
2443 }
2444}
2445
2446void GCS::send_message(enum ap_message id)
2447{
2448 for (uint8_t i=0; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2449 chan(i)->send_message(id);
2450 }
2451}
2452
2453void GCS::update_send()
2454{
2455 update_send_has_been_called = true;
2456
2457 if (!initialised_missionitemprotocol_objects) {
2458 initialised_missionitemprotocol_objects = true;
2459 // once-only initialisation of MissionItemProtocol objects:
2460#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
2461 AP_Mission *mission = AP::mission();
2462 if (mission != nullptr) {
2463 missionitemprotocols[MAV_MISSION_TYPE_MISSION] = new MissionItemProtocol_Waypoints(*mission);
2464 }
2465#endif
2466#if HAL_RALLY_ENABLED
2467 AP_Rally *rally = AP::rally();
2468 if (rally != nullptr) {
2469 missionitemprotocols[MAV_MISSION_TYPE_RALLY] = new MissionItemProtocol_Rally(*rally);
2470 }
2471#endif
2472#if AP_FENCE_ENABLED
2473 AC_Fence *fence = AP::fence();
2474 if (fence != nullptr) {
2475 missionitemprotocols[MAV_MISSION_TYPE_FENCE] = new MissionItemProtocol_Fence(*fence);
2476 }
2477#endif
2478 }
2479
2480 for (auto *prot : missionitemprotocols) {
2481 if (prot == nullptr) {
2482 continue;
2483 }
2484 prot->update();
2485 }
2486
2487 // round-robin the GCS_MAVLINK backend that gets to go first so
2488 // one backend doesn't monopolise all of the time allowed for sending
2489 // messages
2490 for (uint8_t i=first_backend_to_send; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2491 chan(i)->update_send();
2492 }
2493 for (uint8_t i=0; i<first_backend_to_send; i++) {
2494 chan(i)->update_send();
2495 }
2496
2497 service_statustext();
2498
2499 first_backend_to_send++;
2500 if (first_backend_to_send >= num_gcs()) {
2501 first_backend_to_send = 0;
2502 }
2503}
2504
2505void GCS::update_receive(void)
2506{
2507 for (uint8_t i=0; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2508 chan(i)->update_receive();
2509 }
2510 // also update UART pass-thru, if enabled
2511 update_passthru();
2512}
2513
2514void GCS::send_mission_item_reached_message(uint16_t mission_index)
2515{
2516 for (uint8_t i=0; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2517 chan(i)->mission_item_reached_index = mission_index;
2518 chan(i)->send_message(MSG_MISSION_ITEM_REACHED);
2519 }
2520}
2521
2522void GCS::setup_console()
2523{
2524 AP_HAL::UARTDriver *uart = AP::serialmanager().find_serial(AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink, 0);
2525 if (uart == nullptr) {
2526 // this is probably not going to end well.
2527 return;
2528 }
2529 if (ARRAY_SIZE(chan_parameters) == 0) {
2530 return;
2531 }
2532 create_gcs_mavlink_backend(chan_parameters[0], *uart);
2533}
2534
2535
2536GCS_MAVLINK_Parameters::GCS_MAVLINK_Parameters()
2537{
2538 AP_Param::setup_object_defaults(this, var_info);
2539}
2540
2541void GCS::create_gcs_mavlink_backend(GCS_MAVLINK_Parameters &params, AP_HAL::UARTDriver &uart)
2542{
2543 if (_num_gcs >= ARRAY_SIZE(chan_parameters)) {
2544 return;
2545 }
2546 _chan[_num_gcs] = new_gcs_mavlink_backend(params, uart);
2547 if (_chan[_num_gcs] == nullptr) {
2548 return;
2549 }
2550
2551 if (!_chan[_num_gcs]->init(_num_gcs)) {
2552 delete _chan[_num_gcs];
2553 _chan[_num_gcs] = nullptr;
2554 return;
2555 }
2556
2557 _num_gcs++;
2558}
2559
2560void GCS::setup_uarts()
2561{
2562 for (uint8_t i = 1; i < MAVLINK_COMM_NUM_BUFFERS; i++) {
2563 if (i >= ARRAY_SIZE(chan_parameters)) {
2564 // should not happen
2565 break;
2566 }
2567 AP_HAL::UARTDriver *uart = AP::serialmanager().find_serial(AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink, i);
2568 if (uart == nullptr) {
2569 // no more mavlink uarts
2570 break;
2571 }
2572 create_gcs_mavlink_backend(chan_parameters[i], *uart);
2573 }
2574
2575#if AP_FRSKY_TELEM_ENABLED
2576 if (frsky == nullptr) {
2577 frsky = new AP_Frsky_Telem();
2578 if (frsky == nullptr || !frsky->init()) {
2579 delete frsky;
2580 frsky = nullptr;
2581 }
2582 }
2583#endif
2584
2585#if AP_LTM_TELEM_ENABLED
2586 ltm_telemetry.init();
2587#endif
2588
2589#if AP_DEVO_TELEM_ENABLED
2590 devo_telemetry.init();
2591#endif
2592}

2594#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED && AP_MAVLINK_BATTERY2_ENABLED
2595// report battery2 state
2596void GCS_MAVLINK::send_battery2()
2597{
2598 const AP_BattMonitor &battery = AP::battery();
2599
2600 if (battery.num_instances() > 1) {
2601 float current;
2602 if (battery.current_amps(current, 1)) {
2603 current = constrain_float(current * 100,-INT16_MAX,INT16_MAX); // 10*mA
2604 } else {
2605 current = -1;
2606 }
2607 mavlink_msg_battery2_send(chan, battery.voltage(1)*1000, current);
2608 }
2609}
2610#endif // AP_BATTERY_ENABLED && AP_MAVLINK_BATTERY2_ENABLED
2611
2612/*
2613 handle a SET_MODE MAVLink message
2614 */
2615void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_set_mode(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
2616{
2617 mavlink_set_mode_t packet;
2618 mavlink_msg_set_mode_decode(&msg, &packet);
2619
2620 const MAV_MODE _base_mode = (MAV_MODE)packet.base_mode;
2621 const uint32_t _custom_mode = packet.custom_mode;
2622
2623 _set_mode_common(_base_mode, _custom_mode);
2624}
2625
2626/*
2627 code common to both SET_MODE mavlink message and command long set_mode msg
2628*/
2629MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::_set_mode_common(const MAV_MODE _base_mode, const uint32_t _custom_mode)
2630{
2631 // only accept custom modes because there is no easy mapping from Mavlink flight modes to AC flight modes
2632#if AP_VEHICLE_ENABLED
2633 if (uint32_t(_base_mode) & MAV_MODE_FLAG_CUSTOM_MODE_ENABLED) {
2634 if (!AP::vehicle()->set_mode(_custom_mode, ModeReason::GCS_COMMAND)) {
2635 // often we should be returning DENIED rather than FAILED
2636 // here. Perhaps a "has_mode" callback on AP_::vehicle()
2637 // would do?
2638 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2639 }
2640 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
2641 }
2642#endif
2643
2644 if (_base_mode == (MAV_MODE)MAV_MODE_FLAG_DECODE_POSITION_SAFETY) {
2645 // set the safety switch position. Must be in a command by itself
2646 if (_custom_mode == 0) {
2647 // turn safety off (pwm outputs flow to the motors)
2648 hal.rcout->force_safety_off();
2649 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
2650 }
2651 if (_custom_mode == 1) {
2652 // turn safety on (no pwm outputs to the motors)
2653 if (hal.rcout->force_safety_on()) {
2654 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
2655 }
2656 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2657 }
2658 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
2659 }
2660
2661 // Command is invalid (is supported but has invalid parameters)
2662 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
2663}
2664
2665#if AP_OPTICALFLOW_ENABLED
2666/*
2667 send OPTICAL_FLOW message
2668 */
2669void GCS_MAVLINK::send_opticalflow()
2670{
2671 const AP_OpticalFlow *optflow = AP::opticalflow();
2672
2673 // exit immediately if no optical flow sensor or not healthy
2674 if (optflow == nullptr ||
2675 !optflow->healthy()) {
2676 return;
2677 }
2678
2679 // get rates from sensor
2680 const Vector2f &flowRate = optflow->flowRate();
2681 const Vector2f &bodyRate = optflow->bodyRate();
2682
2683 float hagl;
2684 if (!AP::ahrs().get_hagl(hagl)) {
2685 hagl = 0;
2686 }
2687
2688 // populate and send message
2689 mavlink_msg_optical_flow_send(
2690 chan,
2691 AP_HAL::millis(),
2692 0, // sensor id is zero
2693 flowRate.x,
2694 flowRate.y,
2695 flowRate.x - bodyRate.x,
2696 flowRate.y - bodyRate.y,
2697 optflow->quality(),
2698 hagl, // ground distance (in meters) set to zero
2699 flowRate.x,
2700 flowRate.y);
2701}
2702#endif // AP_OPTICALFLOW_ENABLED
2703
2704/*
2705 send AUTOPILOT_VERSION packet
2706 */
2707void GCS_MAVLINK::send_autopilot_version() const
2708{
2709 uint32_t flight_sw_version;
2710 uint32_t middleware_sw_version = 0;
2711#ifdef APJ_BOARD_ID
2712 uint32_t board_version { uint32_t(APJ_BOARD_ID) << 16 };
2713#else
2714 uint32_t board_version = 0;
2715#endif
2716 char flight_custom_version[MAVLINK_MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION_FIELD_FLIGHT_CUSTOM_VERSION_LEN]{};
2717 char middleware_custom_version[MAVLINK_MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION_FIELD_MIDDLEWARE_CUSTOM_VERSION_LEN]{};
2718 char os_custom_version[MAVLINK_MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION_FIELD_OS_CUSTOM_VERSION_LEN]{};
2719#ifdef HAL_USB_VENDOR_ID
2720 const uint16_t vendor_id { HAL_USB_VENDOR_ID };
2721 const uint16_t product_id { HAL_USB_PRODUCT_ID };
2722#else
2723 uint16_t vendor_id = 0;
2724 uint16_t product_id = 0;
2725#endif
2726 uint64_t uid = 0;
2727 uint8_t uid2[MAVLINK_MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION_FIELD_UID2_LEN] = {0};
2728
2729 uint8_t uid_len = sizeof(uid2); // taken as reference and modified
2730 // by following call:
2731 hal.util->get_system_id_unformatted(uid2, uid_len);
2732
2733 const AP_FWVersion &version = AP::fwversion();
2734
2735 flight_sw_version = version.major << (8 * 3) | \
2736 version.minor << (8 * 2) | \
2737 version.patch << (8 * 1) | \
2738 (uint32_t)(version.fw_type) << (8 * 0);
2739
2740 if (version.fw_hash_str) {
2741 strncpy_noterm(flight_custom_version, version.fw_hash_str, ARRAY_SIZE(flight_custom_version));
2742 }
2743
2744 if (version.middleware_hash_str) {
2745 strncpy_noterm(middleware_custom_version, version.middleware_hash_str, ARRAY_SIZE(middleware_custom_version));
2746 }
2747
2748 if (version.os_hash_str) {
2749 strncpy_noterm(os_custom_version, version.os_hash_str, ARRAY_SIZE(os_custom_version));
2750 }
2751
2752 mavlink_msg_autopilot_version_send(
2753 chan,
2754 capabilities(),
2755 flight_sw_version,
2756 middleware_sw_version,
2757 version.os_sw_version,
2758 board_version,
2759 (uint8_t *)flight_custom_version,
2760 (uint8_t *)middleware_custom_version,
2761 (uint8_t *)os_custom_version,
2762 vendor_id,
2763 product_id,
2764 uid,
2765 uid2
2766 );
2767}

2791 velocity.x,

2793 velocity.z);
2794#endif
2795}
