2826#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
2827void GCS_MAVLINK::send_home_position() const
2828{
2829 if (!AP::ahrs().home_is_set()) {
2830 return;
2831 }
2832
2833 const Location &home = AP::ahrs().get_home();
2834
2835 // get home position from origin
2836 Vector3f home_pos_ned;
2837 if (home.get_vector_from_origin_NEU(home_pos_ned)) {
2838 // convert NEU in cm to NED in meters
2839 home_pos_ned *= 0.01f;
2840 home_pos_ned.z *= -1;
2841 } else {
2842 home_pos_ned = Vector3f{NAN, NAN, NAN};
2843 }
2844
2845 const float q[4] {NAN, NAN, NAN, NAN};
2846 mavlink_msg_home_position_send(
2847 chan,
2848 home.lat,
2849 home.lng,
2850 home.alt * 10,
2851 home_pos_ned.x,
2852 home_pos_ned.y,
2853 home_pos_ned.z,
2854 q,
2855 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f,
2856 AP_HAL::micros64());
2857}

2862 if (!AP::ahrs().get_origin(ekf_origin)) {
2863 return;
2864 }
2865 mavlink_msg_gps_global_origin_send(
2866 chan,
2867 ekf_origin.lat,
2868 ekf_origin.lng,
2869 ekf_origin.alt * 10,
2870 AP_HAL::micros64());
2871}
2872#endif // AP_AHRS_ENABLED
2873
2874MAV_STATE GCS_MAVLINK::system_status() const
2875{
2876 MAV_STATE _system_status = vehicle_system_status();
2877 if (_system_status < MAV_STATE_CRITICAL) {
2878 // note that POWEROFF and FLIGHT_TERMINATION are both >
2879 // CRITICAL, so we will not overwrite POWEROFF and
2880 // FLIGHT_TERMINATION even if we have internal errors. If new
2881 // enum entries are added then this may also not overwrite
2882 // those.
2883 if (AP::internalerror().errors()) {
2884 _system_status = MAV_STATE_CRITICAL;
2885 }
2886 }
2887 return _system_status;
2888}

2901 system_status());

2904#if AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
2905MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_aux_function(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
2906{
2907 if (packet.param2 > 2) {
2908 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
2909 }
2910 const RC_Channel::AUX_FUNC aux_func = (RC_Channel::AUX_FUNC)packet.param1;
2911 const RC_Channel::AuxSwitchPos position = (RC_Channel::AuxSwitchPos)packet.param2;
2912 if (!rc().run_aux_function(aux_func, position, RC_Channel::AuxFuncTriggerSource::MAVLINK)) {
2913 // note that this is not quite right; we could be more nuanced
2914 // about our return code here.
2915 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2916 }
2917 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
2918}
2919#endif // AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
2920
2921MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_set_message_interval(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
2922{
2923 return set_message_interval((uint32_t)packet.param1, (int32_t)packet.param2);
2924}
2925
2926MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::set_message_interval(uint32_t msg_id, int32_t interval_us)
2927{
2928 const ap_message id = mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(msg_id);
2929 if (id == MSG_LAST) {
2930 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "No ap_message for mavlink id (%u)", (unsigned int)msg_id);
2931 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
2932 }
2933
2934 uint16_t interval_ms;
2935 if (interval_us == 0) {
2936 // zero is "reset to default rate"
2937 if (!get_default_interval_for_ap_message(id, interval_ms)) {
2938 // if we don't have a default interval then we assume that
2939 // we do not send that message by default. That may not
2940 // be strictly true if some random piece of code has set a
2941 // rate as part of its initialisation - in which case that
2942 // piece of code should probably be adding something into
2943 // whatever get_default_interval_for_ap_message is looking
2944 // at.
2945 interval_ms = 0;
2946 }
2947 } else if (interval_us == -1) {
2948 // minus-one is "stop sending"
2949 interval_ms = 0;
2950 } else if (interval_us < 1000) {
2951 // don't squash sub-ms times to zero
2952 interval_ms = 1;
2953 } else if (interval_us > 60000000) {
2954 interval_ms = 60000;
2955 } else {
2956 interval_ms = interval_us / 1000;
2957 }
2958 if (set_ap_message_interval(id, interval_ms)) {
2959 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
2960 }
2961
2962 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2963}
2964
2965/*
2966 this function is reserved for use by scripting
2967 */
2968MAV_RESULT GCS::set_message_interval(uint8_t port_num, uint32_t msg_id, int32_t interval_us)
2969{
2970 uint8_t channel = get_channel_from_port_number(port_num);
2971
2972 GCS_MAVLINK *link = chan(channel);
2973 if (link == nullptr) {
2974 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2975 }
2976 return link->set_message_interval(msg_id, interval_us);
2977}
2978
2979uint8_t GCS::get_channel_from_port_number(uint8_t port_num)
2980{
2981 const AP_HAL::UARTDriver *u = AP::serialmanager().get_serial_by_id(port_num);
2982 for (uint8_t i=0; i<num_gcs(); i++) {
2983 if (chan(i)->get_uart() == u) {
2984 return i;
2985 }
2986 }
2987
2988 return UINT8_MAX;
2989}
2990
2991MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_request_message(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
2992{
2993 const uint32_t mavlink_id = (uint32_t)packet.param1;
2994 const ap_message id = mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(mavlink_id);
2995 if (id == MSG_LAST) {
2996 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
2997 }
2998 send_message(id);
2999 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3000}
3001
3002bool GCS_MAVLINK::get_ap_message_interval(ap_message id, uint16_t &interval_ms) const
3003{
3004 // check if it's a specially-handled message:
3005 const int8_t deferred_offset = get_deferred_message_index(id);
3006 if (deferred_offset != -1) {
3007 interval_ms = deferred_message[deferred_offset].interval_ms;
3008 return true;
3009 }
3010
3011 // check the deferred message buckets:
3012 for (uint8_t i=0; i<ARRAY_SIZE(deferred_message_bucket); i++) {
3013 const deferred_message_bucket_t &bucket = deferred_message_bucket[i];
3014 if (bucket.ap_message_ids.get(id)) {
3015 interval_ms = bucket.interval_ms;
3016 return true;
3017 }
3018 }
3019
3020 return false;
3021}
3022
3023MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_get_message_interval(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
3024{
3025 if (txspace() < PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, MESSAGE_INTERVAL) + PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, COMMAND_ACK)) {
3026 return MAV_RESULT_TEMPORARILY_REJECTED;
3027 }
3028
3029 const uint32_t mavlink_id = (uint32_t)packet.param1;
3030 if (mavlink_id >= 2 << 15) {
3031 // response packet limits range this works against!
3032 mavlink_msg_message_interval_send(chan, mavlink_id, 0); // not available
3033 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3034 }
3035
3036 const ap_message id = mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(mavlink_id);
3037 if (id == MSG_LAST) {
3038 mavlink_msg_message_interval_send(chan, mavlink_id, 0); // not available
3039 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3040 }
3041
3042 uint16_t interval_ms = 0;
3043 if (!get_ap_message_interval(id, interval_ms)) {
3044 // not streaming this message at the moment...
3045 mavlink_msg_message_interval_send(chan, mavlink_id, -1); // disabled
3046 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3047 }
3048
3049 if (interval_ms == 0) {
3050 mavlink_msg_message_interval_send(chan, mavlink_id, -1); // disabled
3051 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3052 }
3053
3054 mavlink_msg_message_interval_send(chan, mavlink_id, interval_ms * 1000);
3055 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3056}
3057
3058
3059// are we still delaying telemetry to try to avoid Xbee bricking?
3060bool GCS_MAVLINK::telemetry_delayed() const
3061{
3062 uint32_t tnow = AP_HAL::millis() >> 10;
3063 if (tnow > telem_delay()) {
3064 return false;
3065 }
3066 if (chan == MAVLINK_COMM_0 && hal.gpio->usb_connected()) {
3067 // this is USB telemetry, so won't be an Xbee
3068 return false;
3069 }
3070 // we're either on the 2nd UART, or no USB cable is connected
3071 // we need to delay telemetry by the TELEM_DELAY time
3072 return true;
3073}

3075
3076/*
3077 send SERVO_OUTPUT_RAW
3078 */
3079void GCS_MAVLINK::send_servo_output_raw()
3080{
3081 const uint32_t enabled_mask = ~SRV_Channels::get_output_channel_mask(SRV_Channel::k_GPIO);
3082 if (enabled_mask == 0) {
3083 return;
3084 }
3085
3086#if NUM_SERVO_CHANNELS >= 17
3087 static const uint8_t max_channels = 32;
3088#else
3089 static const uint8_t max_channels = 16;
3090#endif
3091
3092 uint16_t values[max_channels] {};
3093 hal.rcout->read(values, max_channels);
3094 for (uint8_t i=0; i<max_channels; i++) {
3095 if (values[i] == 65535) {
3096 values[i] = 0;
3097 }
3098 }
3099 if ((enabled_mask & 0xFFFF) != 0) {
3100 mavlink_msg_servo_output_raw_send(
3101 chan,
3102 AP_HAL::micros(),
3103 0, // port
3104 values[0], values[1], values[2], values[3],
3105 values[4], values[5], values[6], values[7],
3106 values[8], values[9], values[10], values[11],
3107 values[12], values[13], values[14], values[15]);
3108 }
3109
3110#if NUM_SERVO_CHANNELS >= 17
3111 if ((enabled_mask & 0xFFFF0000) != 0) {
3112 mavlink_msg_servo_output_raw_send(
3113 chan,
3114 AP_HAL::micros(),
3115 1, // port
3116 values[16], values[17], values[18], values[19],
3117 values[20], values[21], values[22], values[23],
3118 values[24], values[25], values[26], values[27],
3119 values[28], values[29], values[30], values[31]);
3120 }
3121#endif
3122}

3140float GCS_MAVLINK::vfr_hud_airspeed() const
3141{
3142#if AP_AIRSPEED_ENABLED
3143 AP_Airspeed *airspeed = AP_Airspeed::get_singleton();
3144 if (airspeed != nullptr && airspeed->healthy()) {
3145 return airspeed->get_airspeed();
3146 }
3147#endif
3148
3149#if AP_GPS_ENABLED
3150 // because most vehicles don't have airspeed sensors, we return a
3151 // different sort of speed estimate in the relevant field for
3152 // comparison's sake.
3153 return AP::gps().ground_speed();
3154#endif
3155
3156 return 0.0;
3157}

3159float GCS_MAVLINK::vfr_hud_climbrate() const
3160{
3161#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
3162 Vector3f velned;
3163 if (AP::ahrs().get_velocity_NED(velned) ||
3164 AP::ahrs().get_vert_pos_rate_D(velned.z)) {
3165 return -velned.z;
3166 }
3167#endif
3168 return 0;
3169}
3170
3171float GCS_MAVLINK::vfr_hud_alt() const
3172{
3173 return global_position_current_loc.alt * 0.01f; // cm -> m
3174}
3175
3176void GCS_MAVLINK::send_vfr_hud()
3177{
3178#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
3179 AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
3180
3181 // return values ignored; we send stale data
3182 UNUSED_RESULT(ahrs.get_location(global_position_current_loc));
3183
3184 mavlink_msg_vfr_hud_send(
3185 chan,
3186 vfr_hud_airspeed(),
3187 ahrs.groundspeed(),
3188 (ahrs.yaw_sensor / 100) % 360,
3189 abs(vfr_hud_throttle()),
3190 vfr_hud_alt(),
3191 vfr_hud_climbrate());
3192#endif
3193}
3194
3195/*
3196 handle a MAV_CMD_PREFLIGHT_REBOOT_SHUTDOWN command
3197
3198 Optionally disable PX4IO overrides. This is done for quadplanes to
3199 prevent the mixer running while rebooting which can start the VTOL
3200 motors. That can be dangerous when a preflight reboot is done with
3201 the pilot close to the aircraft and can also damage the aircraft
3202 */
3203MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_preflight_reboot(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3204{
3205 if (is_equal(packet.param1, 42.0f) &&
3206 is_equal(packet.param2, 24.0f) &&
3207 is_equal(packet.param3, 71.0f)) {
3208#if AP_MAVLINK_FAILURE_CREATION_ENABLED
3209 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 93.0f)) {
3210 // this is a magic sequence to force the main loop to
3211 // lockup. This is for testing the stm32 watchdog
3212 // functionality
3213 while (true) {
3214 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"entering lockup");
3215 hal.scheduler->delay(250);
3216 }
3217 }
3218 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 94.0f)) {
3219 // the following text is unlikely to make it out...
3220 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"deferencing a bad thing");
3221
3222#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD != HAL_BOARD_ESP32
3223// esp32 can't do this bit, skip it, return an error
3224 void *foo = (void*)0xE000ED38;
3225
3226 typedef void (*fptr)();
3227 fptr gptr = (fptr) (void *) foo;
3228 gptr();
3229#endif
3230 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3231 }
3232 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 95.0f)) {
3233 // the following text is unlikely to make it out...
3234 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"calling AP_HAL::panic(...)");
3235
3236 AP_HAL::panic("panicing");
3237
3238 // keep calm and carry on
3239 }
3240 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 96.0f)) {
3241 // deliberately corrupt parameter storage
3242 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"wiping parameter storage header");
3243 StorageAccess param_storage{StorageManager::StorageParam};
3244 uint8_t zeros[40] {};
3245 param_storage.write_block(0, zeros, sizeof(zeros));
3246 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3247 }
3248 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 97.0f)) {
3249 // create a really long loop
3250 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"Creating long loop");
3251 // 250ms:
3252 for (uint8_t i=0; i<250; i++) {
3253 hal.scheduler->delay_microseconds(1000);
3254 }
3255 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3256 }
3257 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 98.0f)) {
3258 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"Creating internal error");
3259 INTERNAL_ERROR(AP_InternalError::error_t::flow_of_control);
3260 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3261 }
3262 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 100.0f)) {
3263 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"Creating mutex deadlock");
3264 hal.scheduler->register_io_process(FUNCTOR_BIND_MEMBER(&GCS_MAVLINK::deadlock_sem, void));
3265 while (!_deadlock_sem.taken) {
3266 hal.scheduler->delay(1);
3267 }
3268 WITH_SEMAPHORE(_deadlock_sem.sem);
3269 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING,"deadlock passed");
3270 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3271 }
3272#endif // AP_MAVLINK_FAILURE_CREATION_ENABLED
3273
3274#if HAL_ENABLE_DFU_BOOT
3275 if (is_equal(packet.param4, 99.0f)) {
3276#if AP_SIGNED_FIRMWARE
3277 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_ERROR, "Refusing DFU for secure firmware");
3278 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3279#else
3280 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_WARNING, "Entering DFU mode");
3281 hal.util->boot_to_dfu();
3282 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3283#endif
3284 }
3285#endif
3286 }
3287
3288 // refuse reboot when armed:
3289 if (hal.util->get_soft_armed()) {
3291 const uint32_t magic_force_reboot_value = 20190226;
3292 if (packet.y != magic_force_reboot_value) {
3293 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3294 }
3295 }
3296
3297 if (!(is_equal(packet.param1, 1.0f) || is_equal(packet.param1, 3.0f))) {
3298 // param1 must be 1 or 3 - 1 being reboot, 3 being reboot-to-bootloader
3299 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
3300 }
3301
3302#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
3303 { // autotest relies in receiving the ACK for the reboot. Ensure
3304 // there is space for it:
3305 const uint32_t tstart_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
3306 while (AP_HAL::millis() - tstart_ms < 1000) {
3307 if (HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, COMMAND_ACK)) {
3308 break;
3309 }
3310 hal.scheduler->delay(10);
3311 }
3312 }
3313#endif
3314
3315 // send ack before we reboot
3316 mavlink_msg_command_ack_send(chan, packet.command, MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED,
3317 0, 0,
3318 msg.sysid,
3319 msg.compid);
3320
3321 // when packet.param1 == 3 we reboot to hold in bootloader
3322 const bool hold_in_bootloader = is_equal(packet.param1, 3.0f);
3323
3324#if AP_VEHICLE_ENABLED
3325 AP::vehicle()->reboot(hold_in_bootloader); // not expected to return
3326#else
3327 hal.scheduler->reboot(hold_in_bootloader);
3328#endif
3329
3330 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3331}
3332
3333#if AP_MAVLINK_FAILURE_CREATION_ENABLED
3334/*
3335 take a semaphore and do not release it, triggering a deadlock
3336 */
3337void GCS_MAVLINK::deadlock_sem(void)
3338{
3339 if (!_deadlock_sem.taken) {
3340 _deadlock_sem.taken = true;
3341 _deadlock_sem.sem.take_blocking();
3342 }
3343}
3344#endif

3346/*
3347 handle a flight termination request
3348 */
3349MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_flight_termination(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
3350{
3351#if AP_ADVANCEDFAILSAFE_ENABLED
3352 AP_AdvancedFailsafe *failsafe = AP::advancedfailsafe();
3353 if (failsafe == nullptr) {
3354 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
3355 }
3356
3357 bool should_terminate = packet.param1 > 0.5f;
3358
3359 if (failsafe->gcs_terminate(should_terminate, "GCS request")) {
3360 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3361 }
3362 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3363#else
3364 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
3365#endif
3366}

3368#if AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
3369/*
3370 handle a R/C bind request (for spektrum)
3371 */
3372MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_START_RX_PAIR(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
3373{
3374 // initiate bind procedure. We accept the DSM type from either
3375 // param1 or param2 due to a past mixup with what parameter is the
3376 // right one
3377 if (!RC_Channels::receiver_bind(packet.param2>0?packet.param2:packet.param1)) {
3378 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
3379 }
3380 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
3381}
3382#endif // AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
3383
3384uint64_t GCS_MAVLINK::timesync_receive_timestamp_ns() const
3385{
3386 uint64_t ret = _port->receive_time_constraint_us(PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, TIMESYNC));
3387 if (ret == 0) {
3388 ret = AP_HAL::micros64();
3389 }
3390 return ret*1000LL;
3391}
3392
3393uint64_t GCS_MAVLINK::timesync_timestamp_ns() const
3394{
3395 // we add in our own system id try to ensure we only consider
3396 // responses to our own timesync request messages
3397 return AP_HAL::micros64()*1000LL + mavlink_system.sysid;
3398}
3399
3400/*
3401 return a timesync request
3402 Sends back ts1 as received, and tc1 is the local timestamp in usec
3403 */
3404void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_timesync(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3405{
3406 // decode incoming timesync message
3407 mavlink_timesync_t tsync;
3408 mavlink_msg_timesync_decode(&msg, &tsync);
3409
3410 if (tsync.tc1 != 0) {
3411 // this is a response to a timesync request
3412 if (tsync.ts1 != _timesync_request.sent_ts1) {
3413 // we didn't actually send the request.... or it's a
3414 // response to an ancient request...
3415 return;
3416 }
3417#if 0
3418 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO,
3419 "timesync response sysid=%u (latency=%fms)",
3420 msg.sysid,
3421 round_trip_time_us*0.001f);
3422#endif
3423
3424#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
3425 const uint64_t round_trip_time_us = (timesync_receive_timestamp_ns() - _timesync_request.sent_ts1)*0.001f;
3426 AP_Logger *logger = AP_Logger::get_singleton();
3427 if (logger != nullptr) {
3428 AP::logger().Write(
3429 "TSYN",
3430 "TimeUS,SysID,RTT",
3431 "s-s",
3432 "F-F",
3433 "QBQ",
3434 AP_HAL::micros64(),
3435 msg.sysid,
3436 round_trip_time_us
3437 );
3438 }
3439#endif // HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
3440 return;
3441 }
3442
3443 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, TIMESYNC)) {
3444 // drop this timesync request entirely
3445 return;
3446 }
3447
3448 // create new timesync struct with tc1 field as system time in
3449 // nanoseconds. The client timestamp is as close as possible to
3450 // the time we received the TIMESYNC message.
3451 mavlink_timesync_t rsync;
3452 rsync.tc1 = timesync_receive_timestamp_ns();
3453 rsync.ts1 = tsync.ts1;
3454
3455 // respond with a timesync message
3456 mavlink_msg_timesync_send(
3457 chan,
3458 rsync.tc1,
3459 rsync.ts1
3460 );
3461}
3462
3463/*
3464 * broadcast a timesync message. We may get multiple responses to this request.
3465 */
3466void GCS_MAVLINK::send_timesync()
3467{
3468 _timesync_request.sent_ts1 = timesync_timestamp_ns();
3469 mavlink_msg_timesync_send(
3470 chan,
3471 0,
3472 _timesync_request.sent_ts1
3473 );
3474}
3475
3476void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_statustext(const mavlink_message_t &msg) const
3477{
3478#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
3479 AP_Logger *logger = AP_Logger::get_singleton();
3480 if (logger == nullptr) {
3481 return;
3482 }
3483
3484 mavlink_statustext_t packet;
3485 mavlink_msg_statustext_decode(&msg, &packet);
3486 const uint8_t max_prefix_len = 20;
3487 const uint8_t text_len = MAVLINK_MSG_STATUSTEXT_FIELD_TEXT_LEN+1+max_prefix_len;
3488 char text[text_len] = { 'G','C','S',':'};
3489 uint8_t offset = strlen(text);
3490
3491 if (msg.sysid != sysid_my_gcs()) {
3492 offset = hal.util->snprintf(text,
3493 max_prefix_len,
3494 "SRC=%u/%u:",
3495 msg.sysid,
3496 msg.compid);
3497 offset = MIN(offset, max_prefix_len);
3498 }
3499
3500 memcpy(&text[offset], packet.text, MAVLINK_MSG_STATUSTEXT_FIELD_TEXT_LEN);
3501
3502 logger->Write_Message(text);
3503#endif
3504}

3507/*
3508 handle logging of named values from mavlink.
3509 */
3510void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_named_value(const mavlink_message_t &msg) const
3511{

3518 mavlink_msg_named_value_float_decode(&msg, &p);
3519 char s[11] {};
3520 strncpy(s, p.name, sizeof(s)-1);
3521 logger->Write("NVAL", "TimeUS,TimeBootMS,Name,Value,SSys,SCom", "ss#---", "FC----", "QINfBB",
3522 AP_HAL::micros64(),
3523 p.time_boot_ms,
3524 s,
3525 p.value,
3526 msg.sysid,
3527 msg.compid);
3528#endif
3529}

3554#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
3555// sets ekf_origin if it has not been set.
3556// should only be used when there is no GPS to provide an absolute position
3557void GCS_MAVLINK::set_ekf_origin(const Location& loc)
3558{
3559 // check location is valid
3560 if (!loc.check_latlng()) {
3561 return;
3562 }
3563
3564 AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
3565
3566 // check if EKF origin has already been set
3567 Location ekf_origin;
3568 if (ahrs.get_origin(ekf_origin)) {
3569 return;
3570 }
3571
3572 if (!ahrs.set_origin(loc)) {
3573 return;
3574 }
3575
3576#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
3577 ahrs.Log_Write_Home_And_Origin();
3578#endif
3579
3580 // send ekf origin to GCS
3581 if (!try_send_message(MSG_ORIGIN)) {
3582 // try again later
3583 send_message(MSG_ORIGIN);
3584 }
3585}
3586
3587void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_set_gps_global_origin(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3588{
3589 mavlink_set_gps_global_origin_t packet;
3590 mavlink_msg_set_gps_global_origin_decode(&msg, &packet);
3591
3592 // sanity check location
3593 if (!check_latlng(packet.latitude, packet.longitude)) {
3594 // silently drop the request
3595 return;
3596 }
3597
3598 Location ekf_origin {};
3599 ekf_origin.lat = packet.latitude;
3600 ekf_origin.lng = packet.longitude;
3601 ekf_origin.alt = packet.altitude / 10;
3602 set_ekf_origin(ekf_origin);
3603}
3604#endif // AP_AHRS_ENABLED

3606/*
3607 handle a DATA96 message
3608 */
3609void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_data_packet(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3610{
3611#if HAL_RCINPUT_WITH_AP_RADIO
3612 mavlink_data96_t m;
3613 mavlink_msg_data96_decode(&msg, &m);
3614 switch (m.type) {
3615 case 42:
3616 case 43: {
3617 // pass to AP_Radio (for firmware upload and playing test tunes)
3618 AP_Radio *radio = AP_Radio::get_singleton();
3619 if (radio != nullptr) {
3620 radio->handle_data_packet(chan, m);
3621 }
3622 break;
3623 }
3624 default:
3625 // unknown
3626 break;
3627 }
3628#endif
3629}

3668
3669/*
3670 handle ODOMETRY message. This message combines position, velocity
3671 and attitude data
3672 */
3673void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_odometry(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3674{
3675 AP_VisualOdom *visual_odom = AP::visualodom();
3676 if (visual_odom == nullptr) {
3677 return;
3678 }
3679
3680 mavlink_odometry_t m;
3681 mavlink_msg_odometry_decode(&msg, &m);
3682
3683 if (m.frame_id != MAV_FRAME_LOCAL_FRD ||
3684 m.child_frame_id != MAV_FRAME_BODY_FRD) {
3685 // only support local FRD frame data
3686 return;
3687 }
3688
3689 Quaternion q{m.q[0],m.q[1],m.q[2],m.q[3]};
3690
3691 float posErr = 0;
3692 float angErr = 0;
3693 if (!isnan(m.pose_covariance[0])) {
3694 posErr = cbrtf(sq(m.pose_covariance[0])+sq(m.pose_covariance[6])+sq(m.pose_covariance[11]));
3695 angErr = cbrtf(sq(m.pose_covariance[15])+sq(m.pose_covariance[18])+sq(m.pose_covariance[20]));
3696 }
3697
3698 const uint32_t timestamp_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(m.time_usec, PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, ODOMETRY));
3699 visual_odom->handle_pose_estimate(m.time_usec, timestamp_ms, m.x, m.y, m.z, q, posErr, angErr, m.reset_counter, m.quality);
3700
3701 // convert velocity vector from FRD to NED frame
3702 Vector3f vel{m.vx, m.vy, m.vz};
3703 vel = q * vel;
3704 visual_odom->handle_vision_speed_estimate(m.time_usec, timestamp_ms, vel, m.reset_counter, m.quality);
3705}
3706
3707// there are several messages which all have identical fields in them.
3708// This function provides common handling for the data contained in
3709// these packets
3710void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_common_vision_position_estimate_data(const uint64_t usec,
3711 const float x,
3712 const float y,
3713 const float z,
3714 const float roll,
3715 const float pitch,
3716 const float yaw,
3717 const float covariance[21],
3718 const uint8_t reset_counter,
3719 const uint16_t payload_size)
3720{
3721 float posErr = 0;
3722 float angErr = 0;
3723 // correct offboard timestamp to be in local ms since boot
3724 uint32_t timestamp_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(usec, payload_size);
3725
3726 AP_VisualOdom *visual_odom = AP::visualodom();
3727 if (visual_odom == nullptr) {
3728 return;
3729 }
3730
3731 if (!isnan(covariance[0])) {
3732 posErr = cbrtf(sq(covariance[0])+sq(covariance[6])+sq(covariance[11]));
3733 angErr = cbrtf(sq(covariance[15])+sq(covariance[18])+sq(covariance[20]));
3734 }
3735
3736 visual_odom->handle_pose_estimate(usec, timestamp_ms, x, y, z, roll, pitch, yaw, posErr, angErr, reset_counter, 0);
3737}
3738
3739void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_att_pos_mocap(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3740{
3741 mavlink_att_pos_mocap_t m;
3742 mavlink_msg_att_pos_mocap_decode(&msg, &m);
3743
3744 // correct offboard timestamp to be in local ms since boot
3745 uint32_t timestamp_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(m.time_usec, PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, ATT_POS_MOCAP));
3746
3747 AP_VisualOdom *visual_odom = AP::visualodom();
3748 if (visual_odom == nullptr) {
3749 return;
3750 }
3751 // note: att_pos_mocap does not include reset counter
3752 visual_odom->handle_pose_estimate(m.time_usec, timestamp_ms, m.x, m.y, m.z, m.q, 0, 0, 0, 0);
3753}
3754
3755void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_vision_speed_estimate(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3756{
3757 AP_VisualOdom *visual_odom = AP::visualodom();
3758 if (visual_odom == nullptr) {
3759 return;
3760 }
3761 mavlink_vision_speed_estimate_t m;
3762 mavlink_msg_vision_speed_estimate_decode(&msg, &m);
3763 const Vector3f vel = {m.x, m.y, m.z};
3764 uint32_t timestamp_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(m.usec, PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, VISION_SPEED_ESTIMATE));
3765 visual_odom->handle_vision_speed_estimate(m.usec, timestamp_ms, vel, m.reset_counter, 0);
3766}
3767#endif // HAL_VISUALODOM_ENABLED

3769void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_ack(const mavlink_message_t &msg)

3773 mavlink_msg_command_ack_decode(&msg, &packet);
3774
3775 AP_AccelCal *accelcal = AP::ins().get_acal();
3776 if (accelcal != nullptr) {
3777 accelcal->handle_command_ack(packet);
3778 }
3779#endif
3780}
3781
3782#if AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
3783// allow override of RC channel values for complete GCS
3784// control of switch position and RC PWM values.
3785void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_rc_channels_override(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
3786{
3787 if(msg.sysid != sysid_my_gcs()) {
3788 return; // Only accept control from our gcs
3789 }
3790
3791 const uint32_t tnow = AP_HAL::millis();
3792
3793 mavlink_rc_channels_override_t packet;
3794 mavlink_msg_rc_channels_override_decode(&msg, &packet);
3795
3796 const uint16_t override_data[] = {
3797 packet.chan1_raw,
3798 packet.chan2_raw,
3799 packet.chan3_raw,
3800 packet.chan4_raw,
3801 packet.chan5_raw,
3802 packet.chan6_raw,
3803 packet.chan7_raw,
3804 packet.chan8_raw,
3805 packet.chan9_raw,
3806 packet.chan10_raw,
3807 packet.chan11_raw,
3808 packet.chan12_raw,
3809 packet.chan13_raw,
3810 packet.chan14_raw,
3811 packet.chan15_raw,
3812 packet.chan16_raw
3813 };
3814
3815 for (uint8_t i=0; i<8; i++) {
3816 // Per MAVLink spec a value of UINT16_MAX means to ignore this field.
3817 if (override_data[i] != UINT16_MAX) {
3818 RC_Channels::set_override(i, override_data[i], tnow);
3819 }
3820 }
3821 for (uint8_t i=8; i<ARRAY_SIZE(override_data); i++) {
3822 // Per MAVLink spec a value of zero or UINT16_MAX means to
3823 // ignore this field.
3824 if (override_data[i] != 0 && override_data[i] != UINT16_MAX) {
3825 // per the mavlink spec, a value of UINT16_MAX-1 means
3826 // return the field to RC radio values:
3827 const uint16_t value = override_data[i] == (UINT16_MAX-1) ? 0 : override_data[i];
3828 RC_Channels::set_override(i, value, tnow);
3829 }
3830 }
3831
3832 gcs().sysid_myggcs_seen(tnow);
3833
3834}
3835#endif // AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED

3999 break;
4000#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED

4170 handle_vicon_position_estimate(msg);
4171 break;

4174 handle_odometry(msg);
4175 break;

4183 break;

4188 handle_system_time_message(msg);
4189 break;
4190#endif
4191

4193 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RC_CHANNELS_OVERRIDE:
4194 handle_rc_channels_override(msg);
4195 break;
4196#endif
4197
4198#if AP_OPTICALFLOW_ENABLED
4199 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_OPTICAL_FLOW:
4200 handle_optical_flow(msg);
4201 break;
4202#endif
4203
4204 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_DISTANCE_SENSOR:
4205 handle_distance_sensor(msg);
4206 break;

4210 handle_obstacle_distance(msg);

4214 handle_obstacle_distance_3d(msg);
4215 break;

4220 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_OSD_PARAM_SHOW_CONFIG:
4221 handle_osd_param_config(msg);
4222 break;

4224

4226 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_ADSB_VEHICLE:

4286}
4287
4288void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_common_mission_message(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4289{
4290 switch (msg.msgid) {
4291 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_WRITE_PARTIAL_LIST: // MAV ID: 38
4292 {
4293 handle_mission_write_partial_list(msg);
4294 break;
4295 }
4296
4297 // GCS has sent us a mission item, store to EEPROM
4298 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_ITEM: // MAV ID: 39
4299 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_ITEM_INT:
4300 handle_mission_item(msg);
4301 break;
4302
4303 // read an individual command from EEPROM and send it to the GCS
4304 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_REQUEST_INT:
4305 handle_mission_request_int(msg);
4306 break;
4307
4308#if AP_MAVLINK_MSG_MISSION_REQUEST_ENABLED
4309 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_REQUEST:
4310 handle_mission_request(msg);
4311 break;
4312#endif
4313
4314#if AP_MAVLINK_MISSION_SET_CURRENT_ENABLED
4315 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_SET_CURRENT: // MAV ID: 41
4316 {
4317 AP_Mission *_mission = AP::mission();
4318 if (_mission != nullptr) {
4319 handle_mission_set_current(*_mission, msg);
4320 }
4321 break;
4322 }
4323#endif
4324
4325 // GCS request the full list of commands, we return just the number and leave the GCS to then request each command individually
4326 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_REQUEST_LIST: // MAV ID: 43
4327 {
4328 handle_mission_request_list(msg);
4329 break;
4330 }
4331
4332 // GCS provides the full number of commands it wishes to upload
4333 // individual commands will then be sent from the GCS using the MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_ITEM message
4334 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_COUNT: // MAV ID: 44
4335 {
4336 handle_mission_count(msg);
4337 break;
4338 }
4339
4340 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_CLEAR_ALL: // MAV ID: 45
4341 {
4342 handle_mission_clear_all(msg);
4343 break;
4344 }
4345
4346 case MAVLINK_MSG_ID_MISSION_ACK:
4347 /* not used */
4348 break;
4349 }
4350}
4351
4352#if AP_MAVLINK_AUTOPILOT_VERSION_REQUEST_ENABLED
4353void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_send_autopilot_version(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4354{
4355 send_message(MSG_AUTOPILOT_VERSION);
4356}
4357#endif
4358
4359void GCS_MAVLINK::send_banner()
4360{
4361 // mark the firmware version in the tlog
4362 const AP_FWVersion &fwver = AP::fwversion();
4363
4364 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s", fwver.fw_string);
4365
4366 if (fwver.middleware_name && fwver.os_name) {
4367 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s: %s %s: %s",
4368 fwver.middleware_name, fwver.middleware_hash_str,
4369 fwver.os_name, fwver.os_hash_str);
4370 } else if (fwver.os_name) {
4371 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s: %s",
4372 fwver.os_name, fwver.os_hash_str);
4373 }
4374
4375 // send system ID if we can
4376 char sysid[50];
4377 if (hal.util->get_system_id(sysid)) {
4378 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s", sysid);
4379 }
4380
4381 // send MCUID if we can
4382#if HAL_WITH_IO_MCU
4383#define REVID_MASK 0xFFFF0000
4384#define DEVID_MASK 0xFFF
4385 if (AP_BoardConfig::io_enabled()) {
4386 uint32_t mcuid = iomcu.get_mcu_id();
4387 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "IOMCU: %x %x %lx", uint16_t(mcuid & DEVID_MASK), uint16_t((mcuid & REVID_MASK) >> 16U),
4388 iomcu.get_cpu_id());
4389 }
4390#endif
4391
4392 // send RC output mode info if available
4393 char banner_msg[50];
4394 if (hal.rcout->get_output_mode_banner(banner_msg, sizeof(banner_msg))) {
4395 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s", banner_msg);
4396 }
4397
4398#if AP_INERTIALSENSOR_ENABLED
4399 // output any fast sampling status messages
4400 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < INS_MAX_BACKENDS; i++) {
4401 if (AP::ins().get_output_banner(i, banner_msg, sizeof(banner_msg))) {
4402 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "%s", banner_msg);
4403 }
4404 }
4405#endif
4406}

4429#if AP_BOOTLOADER_FLASHING_ENABLED
4430MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_flash_bootloader(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4431{
4432 if (packet.x != 290876) {
4433 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Magic not set");
4434 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4435 }
4436
4437 switch (hal.util->flash_bootloader()) {
4438 case AP_HAL::Util::FlashBootloader::OK:
4439 case AP_HAL::Util::FlashBootloader::NO_CHANGE:
4440 // consider NO_CHANGE as success (so as not to display error to user)
4441 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4442#if AP_SIGNED_FIRMWARE
4443 case AP_HAL::Util::FlashBootloader::NOT_SIGNED:
4444 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_ERROR, "Bootloader not signed");
4445 break;
4446#endif
4447 default:
4448 break;
4449 }
4450
4451 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4452}
4453#endif // AP_BOOTLOADER_FLASHING_ENABLED
4454
4455MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::_handle_command_preflight_calibration_baro(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4456{
4457 // fast barometer calibration
4458 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Updating barometer calibration");
4459 AP::baro().update_calibration();
4460 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Barometer calibration complete");
4461
4462#if AP_AIRSPEED_ENABLED
4463
4464 AP_Airspeed *airspeed = AP_Airspeed::get_singleton();
4465 if (airspeed != nullptr) {
4466 GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress *task = GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::get_task(MAV_CMD_PREFLIGHT_CALIBRATION, GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::Type::AIRSPEED_CAL, msg.sysid, msg.compid, chan);
4467 if (task == nullptr) {
4468 return MAV_RESULT_TEMPORARILY_REJECTED;
4469 }
4470 airspeed->calibrate(false);
4471 return MAV_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS;
4472 }
4473#endif
4474
4475 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4476}
4477
4478MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::_handle_command_preflight_calibration(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4479{
4480 MAV_RESULT ret = MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4481
4482 EXPECT_DELAY_MS(30000);
4483 if (is_equal(packet.param1,1.0f)) {
4484#if AP_INERTIALSENSOR_ENABLED
4485 if (!AP::ins().calibrate_gyros()) {
4486 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4487 }
4488#else
4489 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4490#endif
4491 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4492 }
4493
4494 if (is_equal(packet.param3,1.0f)) {
4495 return _handle_command_preflight_calibration_baro(msg);
4496 }
4497
4498#if AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
4499 rc().calibrating(is_positive(packet.param4));
4500#endif
4501
4502#if HAL_INS_ACCELCAL_ENABLED
4503 if (packet.x == 1) {
4504 // start with gyro calibration
4505 if (!AP::ins().calibrate_gyros()) {
4506 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4507 }
4508 // start accel cal
4509 AP::ins().acal_init();
4510 AP::ins().get_acal()->start(this);
4511 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4512 }
4513#endif
4514
4515#if AP_INERTIALSENSOR_ENABLED
4516#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
4517 if (packet.x == 2) {
4518 return AP::ins().calibrate_trim();
4519 }
4520#endif
4521
4522 if (packet.x == 4) {
4523 // simple accel calibration
4524 return AP::ins().simple_accel_cal();
4525 }
4526
4527 /*
4528 allow GCS to force an existing calibration of accel and/or
4529 compass to be written as valid. This is useful when reloading
4530 parameters after a full parameter erase
4531 */
4532 if (packet.x == 76) {
4533 // force existing accel calibration to be accepted as valid
4534 AP::ins().force_save_calibration();
4535 ret = MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4536 }
4537#endif // AP_INERTIALSENSOR_ENABLED
4538
4539#if AP_COMPASS_ENABLED
4540 if (is_equal(packet.param2,76.0f)) {
4541 // force existing compass calibration to be accepted as valid
4542 AP::compass().force_save_calibration();
4543 ret = MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4544 }
4545#endif
4546
4547 return ret;
4548}
4549
4550MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_preflight_calibration(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4551{
4552 if (hal.util->get_soft_armed()) {
4553 // *preflight*, remember?
4554 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_NOTICE, "Disarm to allow calibration");
4555 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4556 }
4557 // now call subclass methods:
4558 return _handle_command_preflight_calibration(packet, msg);
4559}

4561#if AP_ARMING_ENABLED
4562MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_run_prearm_checks(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4563{
4564 if (hal.util->get_soft_armed()) {
4565 return MAV_RESULT_TEMPORARILY_REJECTED;
4566 }
4567 (void)AP::arming().pre_arm_checks(true);
4568 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4569}
4570#endif // AP_ARMING_ENABLED
4571
4572#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
4573// changes the current waypoint; at time of writing GCS
4574// implementations use the mavlink message MISSION_SET_CURRENT to set
4575// the current waypoint, rather than this DO command. It is hoped we
4576// can move to this command in the future to avoid acknowledgement
4577// issues with MISSION_SET_CURRENT
4578MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_set_mission_current(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4579{
4580 AP_Mission *mission = AP::mission();
4581 if (mission == nullptr) {
4582 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4583 }
4584
4585 const uint32_t seq = (uint32_t)packet.param1;
4586 if (!mission->is_valid_index(seq)) {
4587 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
4588 }
4589
4590 // From https://mavlink.io/en/messages/common.html#MAV_CMD_DO_SET_MISSION_CURRENT:
4591 // Param 2: Reset Mission
4592 // - Resets mission. 1: true, 0: false. Resets jump counters to initial values
4593 // and changes mission state "completed" to be "active" or "paused".
4594 const bool reset_and_restart = is_equal(packet.param2, 1.0f);
4595 if (reset_and_restart) {
4596 mission->reset();
4597 }
4598 if (!mission->set_current_cmd(seq)) {
4599 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4600 }
4601 if (reset_and_restart) {
4602 mission->resume();
4603 }
4604
4605 // volunteer the new current waypoint for all listeners
4606 send_message(MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT);
4607
4608 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4609}
4610
4611MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_jump_tag(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4612{
4613 AP_Mission *mission = AP::mission();
4614 if (mission == nullptr) {
4615 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4616 }
4617
4618 const uint32_t tag = (uint32_t)packet.param1;
4619 if (tag > UINT16_MAX) {
4620 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
4621 }
4622 if (!mission->jump_to_tag(tag)) {
4623 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4624 }
4625
4626 // volunteer the new current waypoint for all listeners
4627 send_message(MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT);
4628
4629 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4630}
4631#endif

4699{

4702 if ((source_set >= 1) && (source_set <= 3)) {

4704 AP::ahrs().set_posvelyaw_source_set(source_set-1);
4705 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4706 }

4711#if AP_GRIPPER_ENABLED
4712MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_gripper(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4713{
4714 AP_Gripper &gripper = AP::gripper();
4715
4716 // param1 : gripper number (ignored)
4717 // param2 : action (0=release, 1=grab). See GRIPPER_ACTIONS enum.
4718 if(!gripper.enabled()) {
4719 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4720 }
4721
4722 MAV_RESULT result = MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4723
4724 switch ((uint8_t)packet.param2) {
4725 case GRIPPER_ACTION_RELEASE:
4726 gripper.release();
4727 break;
4728 case GRIPPER_ACTION_GRAB:
4729 gripper.grab();
4730 break;
4731 default:
4732 result = MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4733 break;
4734 }
4735
4736 return result;
4737}
4738#endif // AP_GRIPPER_ENABLED

4758#if AP_LANDINGGEAR_ENABLED
4759/*
4760 handle MAV_CMD_AIRFRAME_CONFIGURATION for landing gear control
4761 */
4762MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_airframe_configuration(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4763{
4764 // Param 1: Select which gear, not used in ArduPilot
4765 // Param 2: 0 = Deploy, 1 = Retract
4766 // For safety, anything other than 1 will deploy
4767 AP_LandingGear *lg = AP_LandingGear::get_singleton();
4768 if (lg == nullptr) {
4769 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;

4771 switch ((uint8_t)packet.param2) {
4772 case 1:
4773 lg->set_position(AP_LandingGear::LandingGear_Retract);
4774 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4775 default:
4776 lg->set_position(AP_LandingGear::LandingGear_Deploy);
4777 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4778 }
4779 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4780}

4805#if AP_ARMING_ENABLED
4806MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_component_arm_disarm(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
4807{
4808 if (is_equal(packet.param1,1.0f)) {
4809 if (AP::arming().is_armed()) {
4810 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4811 }
4812 // run pre_arm_checks and arm_checks and display failures
4813 const bool do_arming_checks = !is_equal(packet.param2,magic_force_arm_value);
4814 if (AP::arming().arm(AP_Arming::Method::MAVLINK, do_arming_checks)) {
4815 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4816 }
4817 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4818 }
4819 if (is_zero(packet.param1)) {
4820 if (!AP::arming().is_armed()) {
4821 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4822 }
4823 const bool forced = is_equal(packet.param2, magic_force_disarm_value);
4824 // note disarm()'s second parameter is "do_disarm_checks"
4825 if (AP::arming().disarm(AP_Arming::Method::MAVLINK, !forced)) {
4826 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
4827 }
4828 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
4829 }
4830
4831 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4832}
4833#endif // AP_ARMING_ENABLED
4834
4835bool GCS_MAVLINK::location_from_command_t(const mavlink_command_int_t &in, Location &out)
4836{
4837 if (!command_long_stores_location((MAV_CMD)in.command)) {
4838 return false;
4839 }
4840
4841 // integer storage imposes limits on the altitudes we can accept:
4842 if (isnan(in.z) || fabsf(in.z) > LOCATION_ALT_MAX_M) {
4843 return false;
4844 }
4845
4846 Location::AltFrame frame;
4847 if (!mavlink_coordinate_frame_to_location_alt_frame((MAV_FRAME)in.frame, frame)) {
4848 // unknown coordinate frame
4849 return false;
4850 }
4851
4852 out.lat = in.x;
4853 out.lng = in.y;
4854
4855 out.set_alt_cm(int32_t(in.z * 100), frame);
4856
4857 return true;
4858}
4859
4860bool GCS_MAVLINK::command_long_stores_location(const MAV_CMD command)
4861{
4862 switch(command) {
4863 case MAV_CMD_DO_SET_HOME:
4864 case MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI:
4865 case MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI_LOCATION:
4866 // case MAV_CMD_NAV_TAKEOFF: // technically yes, but we don't do lat/lng
4867 // case MAV_CMD_NAV_VTOL_TAKEOFF:
4868 case MAV_CMD_DO_REPOSITION:
4869 case MAV_CMD_EXTERNAL_POSITION_ESTIMATE:
4870 return true;
4871 default:
4872 return false;
4873 }
4874 return false;
4875}
4876
4877#if AP_MAVLINK_COMMAND_LONG_ENABLED
4878// when conveyed via COMMAND_LONG, a command doesn't come with an
4879// explicit frame. When conveying a location they do have an assumed
4880// frame in ArduPilot, and this function returns that frame.
4881bool GCS_MAVLINK::mav_frame_for_command_long(MAV_FRAME &frame, MAV_CMD packet_command) const
4882{
4883 static const struct {
4884 uint32_t command;
4885 MAV_FRAME frame;
4886 } frame_map[] {
4887 { MAV_CMD_FIXED_MAG_CAL_YAW, MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT },
4888 { MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI, MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT },
4889 { MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI_LOCATION, MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT },
4890 { MAV_CMD_DO_SET_HOME, MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL },
4891 };
4892
4893 // map from command to frame:
4894 for (const auto &map : frame_map) {
4895 if (map.command != packet_command) {
4896 continue;
4897 }
4898 frame = map.frame;
4899 return true;
4900 }
4901
4902 return false;
4903}
4904
4905MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::try_command_long_as_command_int(const mavlink_command_long_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4906{
4907 MAV_FRAME frame = MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT;
4908 if (command_long_stores_location((MAV_CMD)packet.command)) {
4909 // we must be able to supply a frame for the location:
4910 if (!mav_frame_for_command_long(frame, (MAV_CMD)packet.command)) {
4911 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
4912 }
4913 }
4914
4915 // convert and run the command
4916 mavlink_command_int_t command_int;
4917 convert_COMMAND_LONG_to_COMMAND_INT(packet, command_int, frame);
4918
4919 return handle_command_int_packet(command_int, msg);
4920}
4921
4922// returns a value suitable for COMMAND_INT.x or y based on a value
4923// coming in from COMMAND_LONG.p5 or p6:
4924static int32_t convert_COMMAND_LONG_loc_param(float param, bool stores_location)
4925{
4926 if (isnan(param)) {
4927 return 0;
4928 }
4929
4930 if (stores_location) {
4931 return param *1e7;
4932 }
4933
4934 return param;
4935}
4936
4937void GCS_MAVLINK::convert_COMMAND_LONG_to_COMMAND_INT(const mavlink_command_long_t &in, mavlink_command_int_t &out, MAV_FRAME frame)
4938{
4939 out = {};
4940 out.target_system = in.target_system;
4941 out.target_component = in.target_component;
4942 out.frame = frame;
4943 out.command = in.command;
4944 out.current = 0;
4945 out.autocontinue = 0;
4946 out.param1 = in.param1;
4947 out.param2 = in.param2;
4948 out.param3 = in.param3;
4949 out.param4 = in.param4;
4950 const bool stores_location = command_long_stores_location((MAV_CMD)in.command);
4951 out.x = convert_COMMAND_LONG_loc_param(in.param5, stores_location);
4952 out.y = convert_COMMAND_LONG_loc_param(in.param6, stores_location);
4953 out.z = in.param7;
4954}
4955
4956void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_long(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4957{
4958 // decode packet
4959 mavlink_command_long_t packet;
4960 mavlink_msg_command_long_decode(&msg, &packet);
4961
4962#if AP_SCRIPTING_ENABLED
4963 AP_Scripting *scripting = AP_Scripting::get_singleton();
4964 if (scripting != nullptr && scripting->is_handling_command(packet.command)) {
4965 // Scripting has registered to receive this command, do not procces it internaly
4966 return;
4967 }
4968#endif
4969
4970 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_cmd = packet.command;
4971
4972 const MAV_RESULT result = try_command_long_as_command_int(packet, msg);
4973
4974 // send ACK or NAK
4975 mavlink_msg_command_ack_send(chan, packet.command, result,
4976 0, 0,
4977 msg.sysid,
4978 msg.compid);
4979
4980#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
4981 // log the packet:
4982 mavlink_command_int_t packet_int;
4983 convert_COMMAND_LONG_to_COMMAND_INT(packet, packet_int);
4984 AP::logger().Write_Command(packet_int, msg.sysid, msg.compid, result, true);
4985#endif
4986
4987 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_cmd = 0;
4988}
4989
4990#else
4991void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_long(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
4992{
4993 // decode packet
4994 mavlink_command_long_t packet;
4995 mavlink_msg_command_long_decode(&msg, &packet);
4996
4997 // send ACK or NAK
4998 mavlink_msg_command_ack_send(
4999 chan,
5000 packet.command,
5001 MAV_RESULT_COMMAND_INT_ONLY,
5002 0,
5003 0,
5004 msg.sysid,
5005 msg.compid
5006 );
5007
5008}
5009#endif // AP_MAVLINK_COMMAND_LONG_ENABLED
5010
5011MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_set_roi(const Location &roi_loc)
5012{
5013#if HAL_MOUNT_ENABLED
5014 AP_Mount *mount = AP::mount();
5015 if (mount == nullptr) {
5016 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
5017 }
5018
5019 // sanity check location
5020 if (!roi_loc.check_latlng()) {
5021 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5022 }
5023
5024 if (roi_loc.lat == 0 && roi_loc.lng == 0 && roi_loc.alt == 0) {
5025 mount->clear_roi_target();
5026 } else {
5027 mount->set_roi_target(roi_loc);
5028 }
5029 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5030#else
5031 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
5032#endif
5033}
5034
5035
5036void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_landing_target(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
5037{
5038 mavlink_landing_target_t m;
5039 mavlink_msg_landing_target_decode(&msg, &m);
5040 // correct offboard timestamp
5041 const uint32_t corrected_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(m.time_usec, PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, LANDING_TARGET));
5042 handle_landing_target(m, corrected_ms);
5043}
5044
5045
5046MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_set_home(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
5047{
5048 if (is_equal(packet.param1, 1.0f) || (packet.x == 0 && packet.y == 0)) {
5049 // param1 is 1 (or both lat and lon are zero); use current location
5050 if (!set_home_to_current_location(true)) {
5051 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5052 }
5053 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5054 }
5055 // ensure param1 is zero
5056 if (!is_zero(packet.param1)) {
5057 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5058 }
5059 Location new_home_loc;
5060 if (!location_from_command_t(packet, new_home_loc)) {
5061 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
5062 }
5063 if (!set_home(new_home_loc, true)) {
5064 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5065 }
5066 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5067}
5068
5069#if AP_AHRS_POSITION_RESET_ENABLED
5070MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_int_external_position_estimate(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
5071{
5072 if (packet.frame != MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL ||
5073 !isnan(packet.z)) {
5074 // we only support global frame without altitude
5075 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
5076 }
5077
5078 // cope with the NaN when convering to Location
5079 Location loc;
5080 mavlink_command_int_t p2 = packet;
5081 p2.z = 0;
5082
5083 if (!location_from_command_t(p2, loc)) {
5084 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
5085 }
5086 uint32_t timestamp_ms = correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(uint64_t(p2.param1*1e6), PAYLOAD_SIZE(chan, COMMAND_INT));
5087 const uint32_t processing_ms = p2.param2*1e3;
5088 const float pos_accuracy = p2.param3;
5089 if (timestamp_ms > processing_ms) {
5090 timestamp_ms -= processing_ms;
5091 }
5092 if (!AP::ahrs().handle_external_position_estimate(loc, pos_accuracy, timestamp_ms)) {
5093 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5094 }
5095 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5096}
5097#endif // AP_AHRS_POSITION_RESET_ENABLED
5098
5099MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_do_set_roi(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
5100{
5101 // be aware that this method is called for both MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI
5102 // and MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI_LOCATION. If you intend to support any
5103 // of the extra fields in the former then you will need to split
5104 // off support for MAV_CMD_DO_SET_ROI_LOCATION (which doesn't
5105 // support the extra fields).
5106
5107 // param1 : /* Region of interest mode (not used)*/
5108 // param2 : /* MISSION index/ target ID (not used)*/
5109 // param3 : /* ROI index (not used)*/
5110 // param4 : /* empty */
5111 // x : lat
5112 // y : lon
5113 // z : alt
5114 Location roi_loc;
5115 if (!location_from_command_t(packet, roi_loc)) {
5116 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
5117 }
5118 return handle_command_do_set_roi(roi_loc);
5119}

5121#if AP_FILESYSTEM_FORMAT_ENABLED
5122MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_storage_format(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
5123{
5124 if (!is_equal(packet.param1, 1.0f) ||
5125 !is_equal(packet.param2, 1.0f)) {
5126 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
5127 }
5128 GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress *task = GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::get_task(MAV_CMD_STORAGE_FORMAT, GCS_MAVLINK_InProgress::Type::SD_FORMAT, msg.sysid, msg.compid, chan);
5129 if (task == nullptr) {
5130 return MAV_RESULT_TEMPORARILY_REJECTED;
5131 }
5132 if (!AP::FS().format()) {
5133 task->abort();
5134 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5135 }
5136 return MAV_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS;
5137}
5138#endif
5139
5140MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_do_set_safety_switch_state(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet, const mavlink_message_t &msg)
5141{
5142 switch ((SAFETY_SWITCH_STATE)packet.param1) {
5143 case SAFETY_SWITCH_STATE_DANGEROUS:
5144 // turn safety off (pwm outputs flow to the motors)
5145 hal.rcout->force_safety_off();
5146 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5147 case SAFETY_SWITCH_STATE_SAFE:
5148 // turn safety on (no pwm outputs to the motors)
5149 if (hal.rcout->force_safety_on()) {
5150 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
5151 }
5152 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5153 default:
5154 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;
5155 }
5156}

5195 }
5196 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
5197#endif

5200 case MAV_CMD_DO_AUX_FUNCTION:
5201 return handle_command_do_aux_function(packet);
5202#endif
5203
5204#if AP_FENCE_ENABLED
5205 case MAV_CMD_DO_FENCE_ENABLE:
5206 return handle_command_do_fence_enable(packet);
5207#endif
5208
5209 case MAV_CMD_DO_FLIGHTTERMINATION:
5210 return handle_flight_termination(packet);
5211

5213 case MAV_CMD_DO_GRIPPER:

5215#endif

5280#endif

5282 case MAV_CMD_FIXED_MAG_CAL_YAW:
5283 return handle_command_fixed_mag_cal_yaw(packet);

5287 case MAV_CMD_DO_ACCEPT_MAG_CAL:
5288 case MAV_CMD_DO_CANCEL_MAG_CAL:
5289 return handle_command_mag_cal(packet);
5290#endif

5292#if AP_BOOTLOADER_FLASHING_ENABLED
5293 case MAV_CMD_FLASH_BOOTLOADER:
5294 return handle_command_flash_bootloader(packet);
5295#endif

5299 return handle_command_get_home_position(packet);
5300#endif

5309 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;

5311 return MAV_RESULT_DENIED;

5314 return handle_preflight_reboot(packet, msg);

5320 case MAV_CMD_DO_SET_SERVO:

5322 case MAV_CMD_DO_SET_RELAY:
5323 case MAV_CMD_DO_REPEAT_RELAY:

5328 case MAV_CMD_REQUEST_AUTOPILOT_CAPABILITIES:

5330#endif
5331
5332#if AP_ARMING_ENABLED
5333 case MAV_CMD_RUN_PREARM_CHECKS:
5334 return handle_command_run_prearm_checks(packet);
5335#endif

5339 {
5340 AP_Scripting *scripting = AP_Scripting::get_singleton();

5344 return scripting->handle_command_int_packet(packet);

5350 return handle_command_set_ekf_source_set(packet);

5355 return handle_START_RX_PAIR(packet);
5356#endif
5357
5358#if AP_FILESYSTEM_FORMAT_ENABLED
5359 case MAV_CMD_STORAGE_FORMAT:
5360 return handle_command_storage_format(packet, msg);
5361#endif
5362
5363 // support for dealing with streamrate for a specific message and
5364 // requesting a message instance:
5365 case MAV_CMD_SET_MESSAGE_INTERVAL:
5366 return handle_command_set_message_interval(packet);
5367
5368 case MAV_CMD_GET_MESSAGE_INTERVAL:
5369 return handle_command_get_message_interval(packet);
5370
5371 case MAV_CMD_REQUEST_MESSAGE:
5372 return handle_command_request_message(packet);
5373
5374 }
5375
5376 return MAV_RESULT_UNSUPPORTED;
5377}
5378
5379void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_command_int(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
5380{
5381 // decode packet
5382 mavlink_command_int_t packet;
5383 mavlink_msg_command_int_decode(&msg, &packet);
5384
5385#if AP_SCRIPTING_ENABLED
5386 AP_Scripting *scripting = AP_Scripting::get_singleton();
5387 if (scripting != nullptr && scripting->is_handling_command(packet.command)) {
5388 // Scripting has registered to receive this command, do not procces it internaly
5389 return;
5390 }
5391#endif
5392
5393 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_cmd = packet.command;
5394
5395 const MAV_RESULT result = handle_command_int_packet(packet, msg);
5396
5397 // send ACK or NAK
5398 mavlink_msg_command_ack_send(chan, packet.command, result,
5399 0, 0,
5400 msg.sysid,
5401 msg.compid);
5402
5403#if HAL_LOGGING_ENABLED
5404 AP::logger().Write_Command(packet, msg.sysid, msg.compid, result);
5405#endif
5406
5407 hal.util->persistent_data.last_mavlink_cmd = 0;
5408}
5409
5410void GCS::try_send_queued_message_for_type(MAV_MISSION_TYPE type) const {
5411 MissionItemProtocol *prot = get_prot_for_mission_type(type);
5412 if (prot == nullptr) {
5413 return;
5414 }
5415 prot->queued_request_send();
5416}
5417
5418bool GCS_MAVLINK::try_send_mission_message(const enum ap_message id)
5419{
5420 switch (id) {
5421#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
5422 case MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT:
5423 {
5424 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MISSION_CURRENT);
5425 AP_Mission *mission = AP::mission();
5426 if (mission != nullptr) {
5427 send_mission_current(*mission, mission->get_current_nav_index());
5428 }
5429 break;
5430 }
5431 case MSG_MISSION_ITEM_REACHED:
5432 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MISSION_ITEM_REACHED);
5433 mavlink_msg_mission_item_reached_send(chan, mission_item_reached_index);
5434 break;
5435 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_WAYPOINTS:
5436 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MISSION_REQUEST);
5437 gcs().try_send_queued_message_for_type(MAV_MISSION_TYPE_MISSION);
5438 break;
5439#endif
5440#if HAL_RALLY_ENABLED
5441 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_RALLY:
5442 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MISSION_REQUEST);
5443 gcs().try_send_queued_message_for_type(MAV_MISSION_TYPE_RALLY);
5444 break;
5445#endif
5446#if AP_FENCE_ENABLED
5447 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_FENCE:
5448 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MISSION_REQUEST);
5449 gcs().try_send_queued_message_for_type(MAV_MISSION_TYPE_FENCE);
5450 break;
5451#endif
5452 default:
5453 break;
5454 }
5455 return true;
5456}

5463 0);

5466#if AP_RPM_ENABLED
5467void GCS_MAVLINK::send_rpm() const
5468{
5469 AP_RPM *rpm = AP::rpm();
5470 if (rpm == nullptr) {
5471 return;
5472 }
5473
5474 if (!rpm->enabled(0) && !rpm->enabled(1)) {
5475 return;
5476 }
5477
5478 float rpm1 = -1, rpm2 = -1;
5479
5480 rpm->get_rpm(0, rpm1);
5481 rpm->get_rpm(1, rpm2);
5482
5483 mavlink_msg_rpm_send(
5484 chan,
5485 rpm1,
5486 rpm2);
5487}
5488#endif // AP_RPM_ENABLED
5489
5490void GCS_MAVLINK::send_sys_status()
5491{
5492 // send extended status only once vehicle has been initialised
5493 // to avoid unnecessary errors being reported to user
5494 if (!gcs().vehicle_initialised()) {
5495 return;
5496 }
5497#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
5498 const AP_BattMonitor &battery = AP::battery();
5499 float battery_current;
5500 const int8_t battery_remaining = battery_remaining_pct(AP_BATT_PRIMARY_INSTANCE);
5501
5502 if (battery.healthy() && battery.current_amps(battery_current)) {
5503 battery_current = constrain_float(battery_current * 100,-INT16_MAX,INT16_MAX);
5504 } else {
5505 battery_current = -1;
5506 }
5507#endif
5508
5509 uint32_t control_sensors_present;
5510 uint32_t control_sensors_enabled;
5511 uint32_t control_sensors_health;
5512
5513 gcs().get_sensor_status_flags(control_sensors_present, control_sensors_enabled, control_sensors_health);
5514
5515 const uint32_t errors = AP::internalerror().errors();
5516 const uint16_t errors1 = errors & 0xffff;
5517 const uint16_t errors2 = (errors>>16) & 0xffff;
5518 const uint16_t errors4 = AP::internalerror().count() & 0xffff;
5519
5520 mavlink_msg_sys_status_send(
5521 chan,
5522 control_sensors_present,
5523 control_sensors_enabled,
5524 control_sensors_health,
5525#if AP_SCHEDULER_ENABLED
5526 static_cast<uint16_t>(AP::scheduler().load_average() * 1000),
5527#else
5528 0,
5529#endif
5530#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
5531 battery.gcs_voltage() * 1000, // mV
5532 battery_current, // in 10mA units
5533 battery_remaining, // in %
5534#else
5535 0,
5536 -1,
5537 -1,
5538#endif
5539 0, // comm drops %,
5540 0, // comm drops in pkts,
5541 errors1,
5542 errors2,
5543 0, // errors3
5544 errors4); // errors4
5545}
5546
5547void GCS_MAVLINK::send_extended_sys_state() const
5548{
5549 mavlink_msg_extended_sys_state_send(chan, vtol_state(), landed_state());
5550}

5552void GCS_MAVLINK::send_attitude() const
5553{
5554#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5555 const AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
5556 const Vector3f omega = ahrs.get_gyro();
5557 mavlink_msg_attitude_send(
5558 chan,
5559 AP_HAL::millis(),
5560 ahrs.get_roll(),
5561 ahrs.get_pitch(),
5562 ahrs.get_yaw(),
5563 omega.x,
5564 omega.y,
5565 omega.z);
5566#endif
5567}
5568
5569void GCS_MAVLINK::send_attitude_quaternion() const
5570{
5571#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5572 const AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
5573 Quaternion quat;
5574 if (!ahrs.get_quaternion(quat)) {
5575 return;
5576 }
5577 const Vector3f omega = ahrs.get_gyro();
5578 const float repr_offseq_q[] {0,0,0,0}; // unused, but probably should correspond to the AHRS view?
5579 mavlink_msg_attitude_quaternion_send(
5580 chan,
5581 AP_HAL::millis(),
5582 quat.q1,
5583 quat.q2,
5584 quat.q3,
5585 quat.q4,
5586 omega.x, // rollspeed
5587 omega.y, // pitchspeed
5588 omega.z, // yawspeed
5589 repr_offseq_q
5590 );
5591#endif
5592}
5593
5594int32_t GCS_MAVLINK::global_position_int_alt() const {
5595 return global_position_current_loc.alt * 10UL;
5596}
5597int32_t GCS_MAVLINK::global_position_int_relative_alt() const {
5598#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5599 float posD;
5600 AP::ahrs().get_relative_position_D_home(posD);
5601 posD *= -1000.0f; // change from down to up and metres to millimeters
5602 return posD;
5603#else
5604 return 0;
5605#endif
5606}
5607
5608void GCS_MAVLINK::send_global_position_int()
5609{
5610#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5611 AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
5612
5613 UNUSED_RESULT(ahrs.get_location(global_position_current_loc)); // return value ignored; we send stale data
5614
5615 Vector3f vel;
5616 if (!ahrs.get_velocity_NED(vel)) {
5617 vel.zero();
5618 }
5619
5620 mavlink_msg_global_position_int_send(
5621 chan,
5622 AP_HAL::millis(),
5623 global_position_current_loc.lat, // in 1E7 degrees
5624 global_position_current_loc.lng, // in 1E7 degrees
5625 global_position_int_alt(), // millimeters above ground/sea level
5626 global_position_int_relative_alt(), // millimeters above home
5627 vel.x * 100, // X speed cm/s (+ve North)
5628 vel.y * 100, // Y speed cm/s (+ve East)
5629 vel.z * 100, // Z speed cm/s (+ve Down)
5630 ahrs.yaw_sensor); // compass heading in 1/100 degree
5631#endif // AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5632}

5662
5663void GCS_MAVLINK::send_set_position_target_global_int(uint8_t target_system, uint8_t target_component, const Location& loc)
5664{
5665
5666 const uint16_t type_mask = POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_VX_IGNORE | POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_VY_IGNORE | POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_VZ_IGNORE | \
5667 POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_AX_IGNORE | POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_AY_IGNORE | POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_AZ_IGNORE | \
5668 POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_YAW_IGNORE | POSITION_TARGET_TYPEMASK_YAW_RATE_IGNORE;
5669
5670 // convert altitude to relative to home
5671 int32_t rel_alt;
5672 if (!loc.get_alt_cm(Location::AltFrame::ABOVE_HOME, rel_alt)) {
5673 return;
5674 }
5675
5676 mavlink_msg_set_position_target_global_int_send(
5677 chan,
5678 AP_HAL::millis(),
5679 target_system,
5680 target_component,
5681 MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT_INT,
5682 type_mask,
5683 loc.lat,
5684 loc.lng,
5685 rel_alt,
5686 0,0,0, // vx, vy, vz
5687 0,0,0, // ax, ay, az
5688 0,0); // yaw, yaw_rate
5689}

5701
5702#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED && APM_BUILD_TYPE(APM_BUILD_Rover)
5703void GCS_MAVLINK::send_water_depth() const
5704{
5705 if (!HAVE_PAYLOAD_SPACE(chan, WATER_DEPTH)) {
5706 return;
5707 }
5708
5709 RangeFinder *rangefinder = RangeFinder::get_singleton();
5710
5711 if (rangefinder == nullptr || !rangefinder->has_orientation(ROTATION_PITCH_270)){
5712 return;
5713 }
5714
5715 // get position
5716 const AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
5717 Location loc;
5718 IGNORE_RETURN(ahrs.get_location(loc));
5719
5720 for (uint8_t i=0; i<rangefinder->num_sensors(); i++) {
5721 const AP_RangeFinder_Backend *s = rangefinder->get_backend(i);
5722
5723 if (s == nullptr || s->orientation() != ROTATION_PITCH_270 || !s->has_data()) {
5724 continue;
5725 }
5726
5727 // get temperature
5728 float temp_C;
5729 if (!s->get_temp(temp_C)) {
5730 temp_C = 0.0f;
5731 }
5732
5733 const bool sensor_healthy = (s->status() == RangeFinder::Status::Good);
5734
5735 mavlink_msg_water_depth_send(
5736 chan,
5737 AP_HAL::millis(), // time since system boot TODO: take time of measurement
5738 i, // rangefinder instance
5739 sensor_healthy, // sensor healthy
5740 loc.lat, // latitude of vehicle
5741 loc.lng, // longitude of vehicle
5742 loc.alt * 0.01f, // altitude of vehicle (MSL)
5743 ahrs.get_roll(), // roll in radians
5744 ahrs.get_pitch(), // pitch in radians
5745 ahrs.get_yaw(), // yaw in radians
5746 s->distance(), // distance in meters
5747 temp_C); // temperature in degC
5748 }
5749
5750}
5751#endif // AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED && APM_BUILD_TYPE(APM_BUILD_Rover)

5775
5776void GCS_MAVLINK::send_autopilot_state_for_gimbal_device() const
5777{
5778#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5779 // get attitude
5780 const AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
5781 Quaternion quat;
5782 if (!ahrs.get_quaternion(quat)) {
5783 return;
5784 }
5785 const float repr_offseq_q[] = {quat.q1, quat.q2, quat.q3, quat.q4};
5786
5787 // get velocity
5788 Vector3f vel;
5789 if (!ahrs.get_velocity_NED(vel)) {
5790 vel.zero();
5791 }
5792
5793 // get vehicle earth-frame rotation rate targets
5794 Vector3f rate_ef_targets;
5795#if AP_VEHICLE_ENABLED
5796 const AP_Vehicle *vehicle = AP::vehicle();
5797 if (vehicle != nullptr) {
5798 vehicle->get_rate_ef_targets(rate_ef_targets);
5799 }
5800#endif
5801
5802 // get estimator flags
5803 uint16_t est_status_flags = 0;
5804 nav_filter_status nav_filt_status;
5805 if (ahrs.get_filter_status(nav_filt_status)) {
5806 est_status_flags = (uint16_t)(nav_filt_status.value & 0xFFFF);
5807 }
5808
5809 mavlink_msg_autopilot_state_for_gimbal_device_send(
5810 chan,
5811 mavlink_system.sysid, // target system (this autopilot's gimbal)
5812 0, // target component (anything)
5813 AP_HAL::micros(), // time boot us
5814 repr_offseq_q, // attitude as quaternion
5815 0, // attitude estimated delay in micros
5816 vel.x, // x speed in NED (m/s)
5817 vel.y, // y speed in NED (m/s)
5818 vel.z, // z speed in NED (m/s)
5819 0, // velocity estimated delay in micros
5820 rate_ef_targets.z, // feed forward angular velocity z
5821 est_status_flags, // estimator status
5822 0, // landed_state (see MAV_LANDED_STATE)
5823 AP::ahrs().get_yaw_rate_earth()); // [rad/s] Z component of angular velocity in NED (North, East, Down). NaN if unknown
5824#endif // AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5825}
5826
5827void GCS_MAVLINK::send_received_message_deprecation_warning(const char * message)
5828{
5829 // we're not expecting very many of these ever, so a tiny bit of
5830 // de-duping is probably OK:
5831 if (message == last_deprecation_message) {
5832 return;
5833 }
5834
5835 const uint32_t now_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
5836 if (last_deprecation_warning_send_time_ms - now_ms < 30000) {
5837 return;
5838 }
5839 last_deprecation_warning_send_time_ms = now_ms;
5840 last_deprecation_message = message;
5841
5842 send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Received message (%s) is deprecated", message);
5843}
5844
5845bool GCS_MAVLINK::try_send_message(const enum ap_message id)
5846{
5847 bool ret = true;
5848
5849 switch(id) {
5850
5851 case MSG_ATTITUDE:
5852 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(ATTITUDE);
5853 send_attitude();
5854 break;
5855
5856 case MSG_ATTITUDE_QUATERNION:
5857 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(ATTITUDE_QUATERNION);
5858 send_attitude_quaternion();
5859 break;
5860
5861 case MSG_NEXT_PARAM:
5862 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(PARAM_VALUE);
5863 queued_param_send();
5864 break;
5865
5866 case MSG_HEARTBEAT:
5867 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(HEARTBEAT);
5868 last_heartbeat_time = AP_HAL::millis();
5869 send_heartbeat();
5870 break;
5871
5872 case MSG_HWSTATUS:
5873 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(HWSTATUS);
5874 send_hwstatus();
5875 break;
5876
5877 case MSG_LOCATION:
5878 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(GLOBAL_POSITION_INT);
5879 send_global_position_int();
5880 break;
5881
5882#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5883 case MSG_HOME:
5884 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(HOME_POSITION);
5885 send_home_position();
5886 break;
5887
5888 case MSG_ORIGIN:
5889 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(GPS_GLOBAL_ORIGIN);
5890 send_gps_global_origin();
5891 break;
5892#endif // AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5893
5894#if AP_RPM_ENABLED
5895 case MSG_RPM:
5896 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(RPM);
5897 send_rpm();
5898 break;
5899#endif
5900
5901 case MSG_CURRENT_WAYPOINT:
5902 case MSG_MISSION_ITEM_REACHED:
5903 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_WAYPOINTS:
5904 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_RALLY:
5905 case MSG_NEXT_MISSION_REQUEST_FENCE:
5906 ret = try_send_mission_message(id);
5907 break;
5908
5909#if COMPASS_CAL_ENABLED
5910 case MSG_MAG_CAL_PROGRESS:
5911 ret = AP::compass().send_mag_cal_progress(*this);
5912 break;
5913 case MSG_MAG_CAL_REPORT:
5914 ret = AP::compass().send_mag_cal_report(*this);
5915 break;
5916#endif
5917
5918#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
5919 case MSG_BATTERY_STATUS:
5920 send_battery_status();
5921 break;
5922
5923#if AP_MAVLINK_BATTERY2_ENABLED
5924 case MSG_BATTERY2:
5925 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(BATTERY2);
5926 send_battery2();
5927 break;
5928#endif
5929#endif // AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
5930
5931#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
5932 case MSG_EKF_STATUS_REPORT:
5933 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(EKF_STATUS_REPORT);
5934 AP::ahrs().send_ekf_status_report(*this);
5935 break;
5936#endif
5937
5938 case MSG_MEMINFO:
5939 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(MEMINFO);
5940 send_meminfo();
5941 break;
5942
5943#if AP_FENCE_ENABLED
5944 case MSG_FENCE_STATUS:
5945 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(FENCE_STATUS);
5946 send_fence_status();
5947 break;
5948#endif
5949
5950#if AP_RANGEFINDER_ENABLED
5951 case MSG_RANGEFINDER:
5952 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(RANGEFINDER);
5953 send_rangefinder();
5954 break;
5955#endif
5956
5957 case MSG_DISTANCE_SENSOR:
5958 send_distance_sensor();
5959 break;
5960
5961#if AP_CAMERA_ENABLED
5962 case MSG_CAMERA_FEEDBACK:
5963 {
5964 AP_Camera *camera = AP::camera();
5965 if (camera == nullptr) {
5966 break;
5967 }
5968 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(CAMERA_FEEDBACK);
5969 camera->send_feedback(chan);

5971 break;
5972 case MSG_CAMERA_INFORMATION:
5973 {

5976 break;

5978 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(CAMERA_INFORMATION);
5979 camera->send_camera_information(chan);
5980 }
5981 break;
5982 case MSG_CAMERA_SETTINGS:
5983 {

5985 if (camera == nullptr) {
5986 break;
5987 }
5988 CHECK_PAYLOAD_SIZE(CAMERA_SETTINGS);
5989 camera->send_camera_settings(chan);
5990 }
5991 break;
5992#if AP_CAMERA_SEND_FOV_STATUS_ENABLED

6013 break;
