6269#endif
6270
6271#if AP_MAVLINK_MSG_RELAY_STATUS_ENABLED
6272 case MSG_RELAY_STATUS:
6273 ret = send_relay_status();
6274 break;
6275#endif
6276
6277 default:
6278 // try_send_message must always at some stage return true for
6279 // a message, or we will attempt to infinitely retry the
6280 // message as part of send_message.
6281 // This message will be sent out at the same rate as the
6282 // unknown message, so should be safe.
6283 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_DEBUG, "Sending unknown message (%u)", id);
6284#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
6285 AP_HAL::panic("Sending unknown ap_message %u", id);
6286#endif
6287 break;
6288 }
6289
6290 return ret;
6291}
6292
6293uint16_t GCS_MAVLINK::get_interval_for_stream(GCS_MAVLINK::streams id) const
6294{
6295 const int16_t frate = streamRates[id].get();
6296 if (frate == 0) {
6297 return 0;
6298 }
6299 const uint32_t ret = 1000/frate;
6300 if (ret > 60000) {
6301 return 60000;
6302 }
6303 return ret;
6304}
6305
6306void GCS_MAVLINK::initialise_message_intervals_for_stream(GCS_MAVLINK::streams id)
6307{
6308 for (uint8_t i=0; all_stream_entries[i].ap_message_ids != nullptr; i++) {
6309 const GCS_MAVLINK::stream_entries &entries = all_stream_entries[i];
6310 if (entries.stream_id != id) {
6311 continue;
6312 }
6313 // found it!
6314 const uint16_t interval_ms = get_interval_for_stream(id);
6315 for (uint8_t j=0; j<entries.num_ap_message_ids; j++) {
6316 set_ap_message_interval(entries.ap_message_ids[j], interval_ms);
6317 }
6318 break;
6319 }
6320}
6321
6322#if HAL_MAVLINK_INTERVALS_FROM_FILES_ENABLED
6323// open and read contents of path, setting message intervals from each
6324// line
6325DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::DefaultIntervalsFromFiles(uint16_t max_num)
6326{
6327 if (max_num == 0) {
6328 return;
6329 }
6330 _intervals = new from_file_default_interval[max_num];
6331 _max_intervals = max_num;
6332}
6333
6334DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::~DefaultIntervalsFromFiles()
6335{
6336 delete[] (_intervals);
6337}
6338
6339void DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::set(ap_message id, uint16_t interval)
6340{
6341 if (_intervals == nullptr) {
6342 return;
6343 }
6344
6345 // update any existing interval (last-one-in wins)
6346 for (uint8_t i=0; i<_num_intervals; i++) {
6347 if (_intervals[i].id == id) {
6348 _intervals[i].interval = interval;
6349 return;
6350 }
6351 }
6352
6353 // store an interval we've not seen before:
6354 if (_num_intervals == _max_intervals) {
6355 return;
6356 }
6357
6358 _intervals[_num_intervals].id = id;
6359 _intervals[_num_intervals].interval = interval;
6360 _num_intervals++;
6361}
6362
6363bool DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::get_interval_for_ap_message_id(ap_message id, uint16_t &interval) const
6364{
6365 for (uint16_t i=0; i<_num_intervals; i++) {
6366 if (_intervals[i].id == id) {
6367 interval = _intervals[i].interval;
6368 return true;
6369 }
6370 }
6371 return false;
6372}
6373
6374ap_message DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::id_at(uint8_t ofs) const
6375{
6376 if (_intervals == nullptr || ofs >= _num_intervals) {
6377 return MSG_LAST;
6378 }
6379 return _intervals[ofs].id;
6380}
6381
6382uint16_t DefaultIntervalsFromFiles::interval_at(uint8_t ofs) const
6383{
6384 if (_intervals == nullptr || ofs >= _num_intervals) {
6385 return -1; // unsigned-integer wrap
6386 }
6387 return _intervals[ofs].interval;
6388}
6389
6390void GCS_MAVLINK::get_intervals_from_filepath(const char *path, DefaultIntervalsFromFiles &intervals)
6391{
6392 const int f = AP::FS().open(path, O_RDONLY);
6393 if (f == -1) {
6394 return;
6395 }
6396
6397 char line[20];
6398 while (AP::FS().fgets(line, sizeof(line)-1, f)) {
6399 char *saveptr = nullptr;
6400 const char *mavlink_id_str = strtok_r(line, " ", &saveptr);
6401 if (mavlink_id_str == nullptr || strlen(mavlink_id_str) == 0) {
6402 continue;
6403 }
6404 const uint32_t mavlink_id = atoi(mavlink_id_str);
6405
6406 const ap_message msg_id = mavlink_id_to_ap_message_id(mavlink_id);
6407 if (msg_id == MSG_LAST) {
6408 continue;
6409 }
6410
6411 const char *interval_str = strtok_r(nullptr, "\r\n", &saveptr);
6412 if (interval_str == nullptr || strlen(interval_str) == 0) {
6413 continue;
6414 }
6415 const uint16_t interval = atoi(interval_str);
6416
6417 intervals.set(msg_id, interval);
6418 }
6419
6420 AP::FS().close(f);
6421}
6422
6423void GCS_MAVLINK::initialise_message_intervals_from_config_files()
6424{
6425 static const char *path_templates[] {
6426 "@ROMFS/message-intervals-chan%u.txt",
6427 "message-intervals-chan%u.txt"
6428 };
6429
6430 // don't do anything at all if no files exist:
6431 bool exists = false;
6432 for (const char * path_template : path_templates) {
6433 struct stat stats;
6434 char *path;
6435 if (asprintf(&path, path_template, chan) == -1) {
6436 continue;
6437 }
6438 if (AP::FS().stat(path, &stats) < 0) {
6439 free(path);
6440 continue;
6441 }
6442 free(path);
6443 if (stats.st_size == 0) {
6444 continue;
6445 }
6446 exists = true;
6447 break;
6448 }
6449 if (!exists) {
6450 return;
6451 }
6452
6453 // first over-allocate:
6454 DefaultIntervalsFromFiles *overallocated = new DefaultIntervalsFromFiles(128);
6455 if (overallocated == nullptr) {
6456 return;
6457 }
6458 for (const char * path_template : path_templates) {
6459 char *path;
6460 if (asprintf(&path, path_template, chan) == -1) {
6461 continue;
6462 }
6463 get_intervals_from_filepath(path, *overallocated);
6464 free(path);
6465 }
6466
6467 // then allocate just the right number and redo all of the work:
6468 const uint16_t num_required = overallocated->num_intervals();
6469 delete overallocated;
6470 overallocated = nullptr;
6471
6472 default_intervals_from_files = new DefaultIntervalsFromFiles(num_required);
6473 if (default_intervals_from_files == nullptr) {
6474 return;
6475 }
6476 for (const char * path_template : path_templates) {
6477 char *path;
6478 if (asprintf(&path, path_template, chan) == -1) {
6479 continue;
6480 }
6481 get_intervals_from_filepath(path, *default_intervals_from_files);
6482 free(path);
6483 }
6484
6485 // now actually initialise the intervals:
6486 for (uint8_t i=0; i<default_intervals_from_files->num_intervals(); i++) {
6487 const ap_message id = default_intervals_from_files->id_at(i);
6488 if (id == MSG_LAST) {
6489 // internal error
6490 break;
6491 }
6492 const uint16_t interval = default_intervals_from_files->interval_at(i);
6493 set_ap_message_interval(id, interval);
6494 }
6495}
6496#endif
6497
6498void GCS_MAVLINK::initialise_message_intervals_from_streamrates()
6499{
6500 // this is O(n^2), but it's once at boot and across a 10-entry list...
6501 for (uint8_t i=0; all_stream_entries[i].ap_message_ids != nullptr; i++) {
6502 initialise_message_intervals_for_stream(all_stream_entries[i].stream_id);
6503 }
6504#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
6505 if (!is_high_latency_link) {
6506 set_mavlink_message_id_interval(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HEARTBEAT, 1000);
6507 } else {
6508 set_mavlink_message_id_interval(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HIGH_LATENCY2, 5000);
6509 }
6510#else
6511 set_mavlink_message_id_interval(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_HEARTBEAT, 1000);
6512#endif
6513}
6514
6515bool GCS_MAVLINK::get_default_interval_for_ap_message(const ap_message id, uint16_t &interval) const
6516{
6517 if (id == MSG_HEARTBEAT) {
6518 // handle heartbeat requests as a special case because heartbeat is not "streamed"
6519 interval = 1000;
6520 return true;
6521 }
6522
6523#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
6524 if (id == MSG_HIGH_LATENCY2) {
6525 // handle HL2 requests as a special case because HL2 is not "streamed"
6526 interval = 5000;
6527 return true;
6528 }
6529#endif
6530
6531#if HAL_MAVLINK_INTERVALS_FROM_FILES_ENABLED
6532 // a user can specify default rates in files, which are read close
6533 // to vehicle startup
6534 if (default_intervals_from_files != nullptr &&
6535 default_intervals_from_files->get_interval_for_ap_message_id(id, interval)) {
6536 return true;
6537 }
6538#endif
6539
6540 // find which stream this ap_message is in
6541 for (uint8_t i=0; all_stream_entries[i].ap_message_ids != nullptr; i++) {
6542 const GCS_MAVLINK::stream_entries &entries = all_stream_entries[i];
6543 for (uint8_t j=0; j<entries.num_ap_message_ids; j++) {
6544 if (entries.ap_message_ids[j] == id) {
6545 interval = get_interval_for_stream(all_stream_entries[i].stream_id);
6546 return true;
6547 }
6548 }
6549 }
6550 return false;
6551}
6552
6553/*
6554 correct an offboard timestamp in microseconds into a local timestamp
6555 since boot in milliseconds. See the JitterCorrection code for details
6556
6557 Return a value in milliseconds since boot (for use by the EKF)
6558 */
6559uint32_t GCS_MAVLINK::correct_offboard_timestamp_usec_to_ms(uint64_t offboard_usec, uint16_t payload_size)
6560{
6561 uint64_t local_us;
6562 // if the HAL supports it then constrain the latest possible time
6563 // the packet could have been sent by the uart receive time and
6564 // the baudrate and packet size.
6565 uint64_t uart_receive_time = _port->receive_time_constraint_us(payload_size);
6566 if (uart_receive_time != 0) {
6567 local_us = uart_receive_time;
6568 } else {
6569 local_us = AP_HAL::micros64();
6570 }
6571 uint64_t corrected_us = lag_correction.correct_offboard_timestamp_usec(offboard_usec, local_us);
6572
6573 return corrected_us / 1000U;
6574}
6575
6576/*
6577 return true if we will accept this packet. Used to implement SYSID_ENFORCE
6578 */
6579bool GCS_MAVLINK::accept_packet(const mavlink_status_t &status,
6580 const mavlink_message_t &msg) const
6581{
6582 if (msg.sysid == mavlink_system.sysid) {
6583 // accept packets from our own components
6584 // (e.g. mavlink-connected companion computers)
6585 return true;
6586 }
6587
6588 if (msg.sysid == sysid_my_gcs()) {
6589 return true;
6590 }
6591
6592 if (msg.msgid == MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RADIO ||
6593 msg.msgid == MAVLINK_MSG_ID_RADIO_STATUS) {
6594 return true;
6595 }
6596
6597 if (!sysid_enforce()) {
6598 return true;
6599 }
6600
6601 return false;
6602}
6603
6604/*
6605 update UART pass-thru, if enabled
6606 */
6607void GCS::update_passthru(void)
6608{
6609#if APM_BUILD_TYPE(APM_BUILD_UNKNOWN)
6610 // examples don't have AP::serialmanager
6611 return;
6612#endif
6613
6614 WITH_SEMAPHORE(_passthru.sem);
6615 uint32_t now = AP_HAL::millis();
6616 uint32_t baud1, baud2;
6617 bool enabled = AP::serialmanager().get_passthru(_passthru.port1, _passthru.port2, _passthru.timeout_s,
6618 baud1, baud2);
6619 if (enabled && !_passthru.enabled) {
6620 _passthru.start_ms = now;
6621 _passthru.last_ms = 0;
6622 _passthru.enabled = true;
6623 _passthru.last_port1_data_ms = now;
6624 _passthru.baud1 = baud1;
6625 _passthru.baud2 = baud2;
6626 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Passthru enabled");
6627 if (!_passthru.timer_installed) {
6628 _passthru.timer_installed = true;
6629 hal.scheduler->register_timer_process(FUNCTOR_BIND_MEMBER(&GCS::passthru_timer, void));
6630 }
6631 } else if (!enabled && _passthru.enabled) {
6632 _passthru.enabled = false;
6633 _passthru.port1->lock_port(0, 0);
6634 _passthru.port2->lock_port(0, 0);
6635 // Restore original baudrates
6636 if (_passthru.baud1 != baud1) {
6637 _passthru.port1->end();
6638 _passthru.port1->begin(baud1);
6639 }
6640 if (_passthru.baud2 != baud2) {
6641 _passthru.port2->end();
6642 _passthru.port2->begin(baud2);
6643 }
6644 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Passthru disabled");
6645 } else if (enabled &&
6646 _passthru.timeout_s &&
6647 now - _passthru.last_port1_data_ms > uint32_t(_passthru.timeout_s)*1000U) {
6648 // timed out, disable
6649 _passthru.enabled = false;
6650 _passthru.port1->lock_port(0, 0);
6651 _passthru.port2->lock_port(0, 0);
6652 AP::serialmanager().disable_passthru();
6653 // Restore original baudrates
6654 if (_passthru.baud1 != baud1) {
6655 _passthru.port1->end();
6656 _passthru.port1->begin(baud1);
6657 }
6658 if (_passthru.baud2 != baud2) {
6659 _passthru.port2->end();
6660 _passthru.port2->begin(baud2);
6661 }
6662 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Passthru timed out");
6663 }
6664}
6665
6666/*
6667 called at 1kHz to handle pass-thru between SERIA0_PASSTHRU port and hal.console
6668 */
6669void GCS::passthru_timer(void)
6670{
6671 WITH_SEMAPHORE(_passthru.sem);
6672
6673 if (!_passthru.enabled) {
6674 // it has been disabled after starting
6675 return;
6676 }
6677 if (_passthru.start_ms != 0) {
6678 uint32_t now = AP_HAL::millis();
6679 if (now - _passthru.start_ms < 1000) {
6680 // delay for 1s so the reply for the SERIAL0_PASSTHRU param set can be seen by GCS
6681 return;
6682 }
6683 _passthru.start_ms = 0;
6684 _passthru.port1->begin(_passthru.baud1);
6685 _passthru.port2->begin(_passthru.baud2);
6686 }
6687
6688 // while pass-thru is enabled lock both ports. They remain
6689 // locked until disabled again, or reboot
6690 const uint32_t lock_key = 0x3256AB9F;
6691 _passthru.port1->lock_port(lock_key, lock_key);
6692 _passthru.port2->lock_port(lock_key, lock_key);
6693
6694 // Check for requested Baud rates over USB
6695 uint32_t baud = _passthru.port1->get_usb_baud();
6696 if (_passthru.baud2 != baud && baud != 0) {
6697 _passthru.baud2 = baud;
6698 _passthru.port2->end();
6699 _passthru.port2->begin_locked(baud, 0, 0, lock_key);
6700 }
6701
6702 baud = _passthru.port2->get_usb_baud();
6703 if (_passthru.baud1 != baud && baud != 0) {
6704 _passthru.baud1 = baud;
6705 _passthru.port1->end();
6706 _passthru.port1->begin_locked(baud, 0, 0, lock_key);
6707 }
6708
6709 uint8_t buf[64];
6710
6711 // read from port1, and write to port2
6712 int16_t nbytes = _passthru.port1->read_locked(buf, sizeof(buf), lock_key);
6713 if (nbytes > 0) {
6714 _passthru.last_port1_data_ms = AP_HAL::millis();
6715 _passthru.port2->write_locked(buf, nbytes, lock_key);
6716 }
6717
6718 // read from port2, and write to port1
6719 nbytes = _passthru.port2->read_locked(buf, sizeof(buf), lock_key);
6720 if (nbytes > 0) {
6721 _passthru.port1->write_locked(buf, nbytes, lock_key);
6722 }
6723}
6724
6725bool GCS_MAVLINK::mavlink_coordinate_frame_to_location_alt_frame(const MAV_FRAME coordinate_frame, Location::AltFrame &frame)
6726{
6727 switch (coordinate_frame) {
6728 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT: // solo shot manager incorrectly sends RELATIVE_ALT instead of RELATIVE_ALT_INT
6729 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_RELATIVE_ALT_INT:
6730 frame = Location::AltFrame::ABOVE_HOME;
6731 return true;
6732 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_TERRAIN_ALT:
6733 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_TERRAIN_ALT_INT:
6734 frame = Location::AltFrame::ABOVE_TERRAIN;
6735 return true;
6736 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL:
6737 case MAV_FRAME_GLOBAL_INT:
6738 frame = Location::AltFrame::ABSOLUTE;
6739 return true;
6740 default:
6741#if CONFIG_HAL_BOARD == HAL_BOARD_SITL
6742 gcs().send_text(MAV_SEVERITY_INFO, "Unknown mavlink coordinate frame %u", coordinate_frame);
6743#endif
6744 return false;
6745 }
6746}
6747
6748uint64_t GCS_MAVLINK::capabilities() const
6749{
6750 uint64_t ret = MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_PARAM_FLOAT |
6751 MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_COMPASS_CALIBRATION;
6752
6753 const auto mavlink_protocol = uartstate->get_protocol();
6754 if (mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLink2 || mavlink_protocol == AP_SerialManager::SerialProtocol_MAVLinkHL) {
6755 ret |= MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_MAVLINK2;
6756 }
6757
6758#if AP_ADVANCEDFAILSAFE_ENABLED
6759 AP_AdvancedFailsafe *failsafe = AP::advancedfailsafe();
6760 if (failsafe != nullptr && failsafe->enabled()) {
6761 // Copter and Sub may also set this bit as they can always terminate
6762 ret |= MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_FLIGHT_TERMINATION;
6763 }
6764#endif
6765
6766#if HAL_RALLY_ENABLED
6767 if (AP::rally()) {
6768 ret |= MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_MISSION_RALLY;
6769 }
6770#endif
6771
6772#if AP_FENCE_ENABLED
6773 if (AP::fence()) {
6774 ret |= MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_MISSION_FENCE;
6775 }
6776#endif
6777
6778#if AP_MAVLINK_FTP_ENABLED
6779 if (!AP_BoardConfig::ftp_disabled()){ //if ftp disable board option is not set
6780 ret |= MAV_PROTOCOL_CAPABILITY_FTP;
6781 }
6782#endif
6783
6784 return ret;
6785}
6786
6787
6788#if AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
6789void GCS_MAVLINK::manual_override(RC_Channel *c, int16_t value_in, const uint16_t offset, const float scaler, const uint32_t tnow, const bool reversed)
6790{
6791 if (c == nullptr) {
6792 return;
6793 }
6794 int16_t override_value = 0;
6795 if (value_in != INT16_MAX) {
6796 const int16_t radio_min = c->get_radio_min();
6797 const int16_t radio_max = c->get_radio_max();
6798 if (reversed) {
6799 value_in *= -1;
6800 }
6801 override_value = radio_min + (radio_max - radio_min) * (value_in + offset) / scaler;
6802 }
6803 c->set_override(override_value, tnow);
6804}
6805
6806void GCS_MAVLINK::handle_manual_control(const mavlink_message_t &msg)
6807{
6808 if (msg.sysid != sysid_my_gcs()) {
6809 return; // only accept control from our gcs
6810 }
6811
6812 mavlink_manual_control_t packet;
6813 mavlink_msg_manual_control_decode(&msg, &packet);
6814
6815 if (packet.target != gcs().sysid_this_mav()) {
6816 return; // only accept control aimed at us
6817 }
6818
6819 uint32_t tnow = AP_HAL::millis();
6820
6821 handle_manual_control_axes(packet, tnow);
6822
6823 // a manual control message is considered to be a 'heartbeat'
6824 // from the ground station for failsafe purposes
6825 gcs().sysid_myggcs_seen(tnow);
6826}
6827#endif // AP_RC_CHANNEL_ENABLED
6828
6829#if AP_RSSI_ENABLED
6830uint8_t GCS_MAVLINK::receiver_rssi() const
6831{
6832 AP_RSSI *aprssi = AP::rssi();
6833 if (aprssi == nullptr) {
6834 return 255;
6835 }
6836
6837 if (!aprssi->enabled()) {
6838 return 255;
6839 }
6840
6841 // scale across the full valid range
6842 return aprssi->read_receiver_rssi() * 254;
6843}
6844#endif
6845
6846GCS &gcs()
6847{
6848 return *GCS::get_singleton();
6849}
6850
6851/*
6852 send HIGH_LATENCY2 message
6853 */
6854#if HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
6855void GCS_MAVLINK::send_high_latency2() const
6856{
6857#if AP_AHRS_ENABLED
6858 AP_AHRS &ahrs = AP::ahrs();
6859 Location global_position_current;
6860 UNUSED_RESULT(ahrs.get_location(global_position_current));
6861#if AP_BATTERY_ENABLED
6862 const int8_t battery_remaining = battery_remaining_pct(AP_BATT_PRIMARY_INSTANCE);
6863#endif
6864
6865 uint16_t current_waypoint = 0;
6866#if AP_MISSION_ENABLED
6867 AP_Mission *mission = AP::mission();
6868 if (mission != nullptr) {
6869 current_waypoint = mission->get_current_nav_index();
6870 }
6871#endif
6872
6873 uint32_t present;
6874 uint32_t enabled;
6875 uint32_t health;
6876 gcs().get_sensor_status_flags(present, enabled, health);
6877 // Remap HL_FAILURE_FLAG from system status flags
6878 static const struct PACKED status_map_t {
6879 MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR sensor;
6880 HL_FAILURE_FLAG failure_flag;
6881 } status_map[] {
6882 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_GPS, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_GPS },
6883 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_DIFFERENTIAL_PRESSURE, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_DIFFERENTIAL_PRESSURE },
6884 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_ABSOLUTE_PRESSURE, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_ABSOLUTE_PRESSURE },
6885 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_3D_ACCEL, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_3D_ACCEL },
6886 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_3D_GYRO, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_3D_GYRO },
6887 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_3D_MAG, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_3D_MAG },
6888 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_TERRAIN, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_TERRAIN },
6889 { MAV_SYS_STATUS_SENSOR_BATTERY, HL_FAILURE_FLAG_BATTERY },

6899 }

6939int8_t GCS_MAVLINK::high_latency_air_temperature() const
6940{
6941#if AP_AIRSPEED_ENABLED
6942 // return units are degC
6943 AP_Airspeed *airspeed = AP_Airspeed::get_singleton();
6944 float air_temperature;
6945 if (airspeed != nullptr && airspeed->enabled() && airspeed->get_temperature(air_temperature)) {
6946 return air_temperature;
6947 }
6948#endif
6949
6950 return INT8_MIN;
6951}
6952
6953/*
6954 handle a MAV_CMD_CONTROL_HIGH_LATENCY command
6955
6956 Enable or disable any marked (via SERIALn_PROTOCOL) high latency connections
6957 */
6958MAV_RESULT GCS_MAVLINK::handle_control_high_latency(const mavlink_command_int_t &packet)
6959{
6960 // high latency mode is enabled if param1=1 or disabled if param1=0
6961 if (is_equal(packet.param1, 0.0f)) {
6962 gcs().enable_high_latency_connections(false);
6963 } else if (is_equal(packet.param1, 1.0f)) {
6964 gcs().enable_high_latency_connections(true);
6965 } else {
6966 return MAV_RESULT_FAILED;
6967 }
6968
6969 // send to all other mavlink components with same sysid
6970 mavlink_command_long_t hl_msg{};
6971 hl_msg.command = MAV_CMD_CONTROL_HIGH_LATENCY;
6972 hl_msg.param1 = packet.param1;
6973 GCS_MAVLINK::send_to_components(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_COMMAND_LONG, (char*)&hl_msg, sizeof(hl_msg));
6974
6975 return MAV_RESULT_ACCEPTED;
6976}
6977#endif // HAL_HIGH_LATENCY2_ENABLED
6978
6979#endif // HAL_GCS_ENABLED
